00:00:47.080 --> 00:00:50.440 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE MORTER: Why is it we think
of healing as a solo journey?

00:00:50.440 --> 00:00:53.170 align:middle line:10%
What if our mental, physical,
and spiritual health

00:00:53.170 --> 00:00:56.770 align:middle line:10%
can be improved simultaneously
through dance, music,

00:00:56.770 --> 00:00:59.350 align:middle line:10%
socialization, and community?

00:00:59.350 --> 00:01:03.730 align:middle line:84%
Today, we have Nii Armah Sowah,
an arts educator and instructor

00:01:03.730 --> 00:01:07.090 align:middle line:84%
at the University of Colorado
and director and founder

00:01:07.090 --> 00:01:09.790 align:middle line:90%
of the 1000 Voices Project.

00:01:09.790 --> 00:01:10.952 align:middle line:90%
Welcome, Nii Armah.

00:01:10.952 --> 00:01:12.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NII ARMAH SOWAH: Thank you.

00:01:12.160 --> 00:01:14.150 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: It is such a
joy to have you here.

00:01:14.150 --> 00:01:15.520 align:middle line:90%
Let me just first say this.

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:19.390 align:middle line:84%
You look so extroverted
and free and liberated.

00:01:19.390 --> 00:01:20.890 align:middle line:90%
Has it always been that way?

00:01:20.890 --> 00:01:23.440 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Well, I
was born in Ghana.

00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:28.930 align:middle line:84%
And I lived and studied
in Ghana till I was older,

00:01:28.930 --> 00:01:31.780 align:middle line:84%
before I moved to
the United States

00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:33.550 align:middle line:90%
to go to graduate school.

00:01:33.550 --> 00:01:37.440 align:middle line:10%
I grew up in a small town
which is part of Accra.

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:41.080 align:middle line:84%
Accra is a metropolitan
city, the capital.

00:01:41.080 --> 00:01:46.120 align:middle line:84%
And my lifestyle, my daily
occupation, what I did mostly

00:01:46.120 --> 00:01:53.020 align:middle line:84%
had to do with going to school,
play, and helping with chores.

00:01:53.020 --> 00:01:55.240 align:middle line:84%
I grew up as a
typical African who

00:01:55.240 --> 00:01:58.990 align:middle line:84%
participated in the
daily life of the home,

00:01:58.990 --> 00:02:00.880 align:middle line:84%
besides going to
school and playing.

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:01.680 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:01.680 --> 00:02:03.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So following
along, contributing--

00:02:03.970 --> 00:02:06.130 align:middle line:90%
not necessarily extroverted.

00:02:06.130 --> 00:02:07.480 align:middle line:90%
Were you the opposite?

00:02:07.480 --> 00:02:08.920 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Well, I
grew up very shy.

00:02:08.920 --> 00:02:09.720 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Shy.

00:02:09.720 --> 00:02:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I remember, as a
kid, I was not one to be seen.

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:19.600 align:middle line:84%
I would mostly lay
back in most contexts.

00:02:19.600 --> 00:02:23.260 align:middle line:10%
And for example,
when I was in school,

00:02:23.260 --> 00:02:26.840 align:middle line:10%
if my teacher sent me to
get a chalk or a duster

00:02:26.840 --> 00:02:31.540 align:middle line:10%
out from another class, the
idea of entering another class

00:02:31.540 --> 00:02:35.080 align:middle line:10%
with all the kids seated and
me speaking with a teacher

00:02:35.080 --> 00:02:36.340 align:middle line:10%
was too much for me.

00:02:36.340 --> 00:02:36.445 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Overwhelming.

00:02:36.445 --> 00:02:38.237 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Instead of
going to another class,

00:02:38.237 --> 00:02:39.090 align:middle line:90%
I'd rather go home.

00:02:39.090 --> 00:02:39.890 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: I get it.

00:02:39.890 --> 00:02:42.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So I ditched
school instead

00:02:42.290 --> 00:02:43.940 align:middle line:90%
of going to another class.

00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:46.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Just didn't want to be
seen-- just retreat, reserved.

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:48.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yup, mm-hmm.

00:02:48.140 --> 00:02:53.470 align:middle line:84%
And I remember when I was young,
if I went to church I would not

00:02:53.470 --> 00:02:57.200 align:middle line:84%
walk through the church to
sit where the usher wanted

00:02:57.200 --> 00:02:58.000 align:middle line:90%
me to sit.

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:02.030 align:middle line:84%
I would sit where I would
have the least exposure.

00:03:02.030 --> 00:03:04.960 align:middle line:84%
And if that meant standing
in the back, that was fine.

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:07.902 align:middle line:90%
I would not be found walking--

00:03:07.902 --> 00:03:08.735 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: I understand.

00:03:08.735 --> 00:03:09.680 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: --when a
crowd was seated.

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:11.120 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: This is my
story as a kid.

00:03:11.120 --> 00:03:11.700 align:middle line:90%
I get this.

00:03:11.700 --> 00:03:11.930 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: For real.

00:03:11.930 --> 00:03:12.530 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: I get it.

00:03:12.530 --> 00:03:12.650 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:13.900 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Didn't want to be seen.

00:03:13.900 --> 00:03:16.910 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So I was
that shy, yeah.

00:03:16.910 --> 00:03:20.810 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So, shy, don't
want to be seen,

00:03:20.810 --> 00:03:25.325 align:middle line:84%
and yet you chose to become
a dancer and then a teacher.

00:03:25.325 --> 00:03:30.705 align:middle line:84%
So can you give us the path
that unfolded that way?

00:03:30.705 --> 00:03:32.330 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Well, I
never imagined I would

00:03:32.330 --> 00:03:34.730 align:middle line:90%
be a dance teacher as a kid.

00:03:34.730 --> 00:03:37.730 align:middle line:84%
I never even imagined
being a dancer

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:41.970 align:middle line:84%
because I remember,
as a child, I

00:03:41.970 --> 00:03:49.890 align:middle line:84%
was not open to doing recitals
in church or in school.

00:03:49.890 --> 00:03:54.330 align:middle line:84%
But I was always open to
dancing, open to singing.

00:03:54.330 --> 00:03:56.010 align:middle line:90%
So I was in the school choir.

00:03:56.010 --> 00:03:59.370 align:middle line:84%
And if there was a play,
I'll be the dancer.

00:03:59.370 --> 00:04:04.380 align:middle line:84%
But talking was not
part of my thing.

00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:08.910 align:middle line:84%
And I never imagined
becoming a dancer.

00:04:08.910 --> 00:04:13.140 align:middle line:84%
One thing I learned early was
that any time I was involved

00:04:13.140 --> 00:04:15.750 align:middle line:90%
in dancing, I felt freer.

00:04:15.750 --> 00:04:20.278 align:middle line:84%
My shyness and
inhibitions went down.

00:04:20.278 --> 00:04:21.695 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Would go
away-- would melt.

00:04:21.695 --> 00:04:25.110 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So that was the
signal for me at an early age,

00:04:25.110 --> 00:04:28.660 align:middle line:84%
that when I danced,
it empowered me.

00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:29.460 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yes.

00:04:29.460 --> 00:04:30.300 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:32.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And this is ultimately
what we all have to find,

00:04:32.760 --> 00:04:36.000 align:middle line:84%
is how do we feel that
sense of empowerment.

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:37.860 align:middle line:84%
If we're ever going
to find our wholeness,

00:04:37.860 --> 00:04:41.410 align:middle line:84%
to heal or to be thriving in
expressing ourselves fully,

00:04:41.410 --> 00:04:43.330 align:middle line:90%
we have to find our way.

00:04:43.330 --> 00:04:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And I find-- I've been 30
years in clinical research

00:04:46.410 --> 00:04:48.390 align:middle line:84%
and clinical practice
and working with people

00:04:48.390 --> 00:04:49.350 align:middle line:90%
in healing--

00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:52.080 align:middle line:84%
that when people
can feel themselves

00:04:52.080 --> 00:04:54.030 align:middle line:90%
in the body, things change.

00:04:54.030 --> 00:04:56.900 align:middle line:84%
And I look forward to
digging into our conversation

00:04:56.900 --> 00:04:57.700 align:middle line:90%
in this way.

00:04:57.700 --> 00:04:57.745 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Sure.

00:04:57.745 --> 00:04:59.430 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Now, first
let's just say this.

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:03.840 align:middle line:84%
When you were 30,
you came to the US

00:05:03.840 --> 00:05:05.540 align:middle line:90%
and found a community here.

00:05:05.540 --> 00:05:06.540 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: I would say 33.

00:05:06.540 --> 00:05:07.150 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: 33.

00:05:07.150 --> 00:05:07.400 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:08.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: OK.

00:05:08.140 --> 00:05:08.940 align:middle line:90%
33.

00:05:08.940 --> 00:05:11.130 align:middle line:84%
Came to the US, moved
into a community

00:05:11.130 --> 00:05:13.830 align:middle line:90%
of people living here.

00:05:13.830 --> 00:05:16.170 align:middle line:84%
What did you notice
about the people that

00:05:16.170 --> 00:05:19.860 align:middle line:84%
were surrounding you
here in this new country

00:05:19.860 --> 00:05:22.110 align:middle line:90%
that you hadn't seen before?

00:05:22.110 --> 00:05:23.190 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Wow.

00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:31.052 align:middle line:84%
Well, I landed in Boston
in 1994 in the blizzard.

00:05:31.052 --> 00:05:31.867 align:middle line:10%
>>SUE: Mm.

00:05:31.867 --> 00:05:32.667 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH] How fun.

00:05:32.667 --> 00:05:33.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: A January blizzard--

00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:34.640 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Wow.

00:05:34.640 --> 00:05:36.660 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --with not much on me--

00:05:36.660 --> 00:05:41.950 align:middle line:84%
lost all my luggage
and had my hand luggage

00:05:41.950 --> 00:05:44.040 align:middle line:90%
with $80 in my pocket.

00:05:44.040 --> 00:05:45.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: $80 in your pocket.

00:05:45.420 --> 00:05:48.280 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Within
the next few weeks,

00:05:48.280 --> 00:05:54.260 align:middle line:84%
my experiences socially in
the streets of Cambridge,

00:05:54.260 --> 00:05:59.120 align:middle line:90%
Massachusetts, transformed me.

00:05:59.120 --> 00:06:04.740 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know before
coming here that it

00:06:04.740 --> 00:06:07.710 align:middle line:90%
mattered that I was black.

00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:14.790 align:middle line:10%
I didn't know that a person's
value had to do with--

00:06:14.790 --> 00:06:17.730 align:middle line:10%


00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:20.480 align:middle line:10%
>>SUE: Anything.

00:06:20.480 --> 00:06:22.480 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: And before coming
here, I was an actor.

00:06:22.480 --> 00:06:24.920 align:middle line:84%
I was a teacher at
that university.

00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:27.700 align:middle line:90%
So I had some self-dignity--

00:06:27.700 --> 00:06:29.200 align:middle line:90%
a sense of dignity.

00:06:29.200 --> 00:06:35.360 align:middle line:84%
But arriving and having people
get up when I sat on the train,

00:06:35.360 --> 00:06:40.768 align:middle line:84%
or feeling lost in the
winter in the Harvard Square

00:06:40.768 --> 00:06:42.560 align:middle line:84%
and trying to get
direction and people just

00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:47.960 align:middle line:84%
walking away from me,
and feeling so alone

00:06:47.960 --> 00:06:53.520 align:middle line:84%
was the most traumatic thing
I ever experienced in my life.

00:06:53.520 --> 00:06:56.812 align:middle line:84%
And I never imagined
it was possible.

00:06:56.812 --> 00:07:01.320 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So you turned inward
then, thinking, separation--

00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:03.990 align:middle line:84%
there's something
different here--

00:07:03.990 --> 00:07:05.670 align:middle line:84%
maybe not knowing
you had medicine

00:07:05.670 --> 00:07:09.150 align:middle line:84%
to bring to a culture that
would behave in such a way.

00:07:09.150 --> 00:07:13.493 align:middle line:10%
In those initial moments, we
tend to respond differently.

00:07:13.493 --> 00:07:14.910 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I think
in the beginning,

00:07:14.910 --> 00:07:16.710 align:middle line:84%
I had a lot of
questions and wondered

00:07:16.710 --> 00:07:20.550 align:middle line:84%
why people would tell me
to call them to have coffee

00:07:20.550 --> 00:07:22.500 align:middle line:90%
if they didn't mean it.

00:07:22.500 --> 00:07:26.580 align:middle line:84%
Because when somebody said, oh,
let's talk, let's make a date,

00:07:26.580 --> 00:07:27.570 align:middle line:90%
I would follow through.

00:07:27.570 --> 00:07:28.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Where you came
from, they meant it.

00:07:28.890 --> 00:07:29.310 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:07:29.310 --> 00:07:30.435 align:middle line:90%
And so I would call people.

00:07:30.435 --> 00:07:33.060 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing I would hear
is, I don't know what he wants.

00:07:33.060 --> 00:07:33.900 align:middle line:90%
He keeps calling me.

00:07:33.900 --> 00:07:37.140 align:middle line:84%
Well, I thought we had a deal,
I was supposed to call you.

00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:41.160 align:middle line:84%
So after a while, I've
realized that it was not

00:07:41.160 --> 00:07:42.640 align:middle line:90%
meant like that.

00:07:42.640 --> 00:07:44.670 align:middle line:90%
It was just talk.

00:07:44.670 --> 00:07:47.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: You mentioned that
several people in the community

00:07:47.610 --> 00:07:51.810 align:middle line:84%
that you arrived in and started
to establish this new life

00:07:51.810 --> 00:07:54.370 align:middle line:90%
within were in therapy.

00:07:54.370 --> 00:07:55.290 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Oh.

00:07:55.290 --> 00:07:58.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, I was in graduate school
for expressive arts therapies.

00:07:58.290 --> 00:08:00.720 align:middle line:84%
I went to Lesley
University in Cambridge.

00:08:00.720 --> 00:08:04.830 align:middle line:84%
And so I was in a program
with students studying

00:08:04.830 --> 00:08:06.570 align:middle line:84%
counseling and
psychology, students

00:08:06.570 --> 00:08:09.900 align:middle line:84%
studying dance therapy,
art therapy, music therapy,

00:08:09.900 --> 00:08:11.190 align:middle line:90%
psychodrama.

00:08:11.190 --> 00:08:18.190 align:middle line:10%
And I came in as an expressive
arts therapy student

00:08:18.190 --> 00:08:21.220 align:middle line:10%
with emphasis on dance therapy.

00:08:21.220 --> 00:08:25.570 align:middle line:84%
And as the semester went
by, I learned quickly

00:08:25.570 --> 00:08:31.360 align:middle line:84%
that the concepts and the
philosophies that the program

00:08:31.360 --> 00:08:39.470 align:middle line:84%
were founded on were not
aligned with my background

00:08:39.470 --> 00:08:41.450 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what
dance therapy was

00:08:41.450 --> 00:08:44.980 align:middle line:84%
or what psychological
models we were using--

00:08:44.980 --> 00:08:48.030 align:middle line:84%
were not aligned to
where I was coming from.

00:08:48.030 --> 00:08:51.740 align:middle line:84%
So I started questioning
how much of this education

00:08:51.740 --> 00:09:00.030 align:middle line:84%
to embrace, how much of this
program to get buried in.

00:09:00.030 --> 00:09:04.080 align:middle line:84%
So I started questioning things
and making choices carefully so

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:06.670 align:middle line:90%
that I didn't lose my identity.

00:09:06.670 --> 00:09:07.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yes.

00:09:07.470 --> 00:09:08.270 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:09:08.270 --> 00:09:10.030 align:middle line:90%
So that's why I came in.

00:09:10.030 --> 00:09:14.880 align:middle line:84%
And as a result, I started
a program on the campus.

00:09:14.880 --> 00:09:17.810 align:middle line:84%
It was a Friday
evening thing that I

00:09:17.810 --> 00:09:22.390 align:middle line:84%
offered to the community--
the whole campus--

00:09:22.390 --> 00:09:25.460 align:middle line:90%
students, faculty, staff.

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:30.130 align:middle line:84%
And I did that for a couple
of years, Friday evenings.

00:09:30.130 --> 00:09:33.850 align:middle line:84%
And people would come, and we
would dance, we would drum,

00:09:33.850 --> 00:09:38.550 align:middle line:84%
we would sing, some
massage, chat, also sorts

00:09:38.550 --> 00:09:44.560 align:middle line:90%
of just human activities.

00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:49.060 align:middle line:84%
And what I learned
from that, from talking

00:09:49.060 --> 00:09:53.880 align:middle line:84%
to my participants
and my peers was

00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:58.950 align:middle line:84%
that even though most
of them were therapists,

00:09:58.950 --> 00:10:02.190 align:middle line:84%
they were therapists
in training.

00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:05.040 align:middle line:84%
They found that
coming to my event

00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:10.530 align:middle line:84%
was more healing, more
fulfilling, more empowering.

00:10:10.530 --> 00:10:12.330 align:middle line:84%
And if they didn't
have that, they

00:10:12.330 --> 00:10:14.250 align:middle line:90%
would be losing their minds.

00:10:14.250 --> 00:10:17.262 align:middle line:84%
Because they went in as
therapists to help people,

00:10:17.262 --> 00:10:18.720 align:middle line:84%
but they realized
they, themselves,

00:10:18.720 --> 00:10:19.927 align:middle line:90%
needed a lot of help.

00:10:19.927 --> 00:10:21.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Were drawn
to the things that--

00:10:21.510 --> 00:10:25.110 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: And they found
what I did very powerful.

00:10:25.110 --> 00:10:30.210 align:middle line:84%
And at the time, I
didn't have any set ideas

00:10:30.210 --> 00:10:32.560 align:middle line:90%
of exactly what I was doing.

00:10:32.560 --> 00:10:34.950 align:middle line:84%
But I was just drawing
from my background

00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:40.190 align:middle line:84%
and a little from my training
and piecing it together.

00:10:40.190 --> 00:10:43.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Yes, you were discovering
your true soul's calling,

00:10:43.740 --> 00:10:44.670 align:middle line:90%
your true path.

00:10:44.670 --> 00:10:45.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:10:45.470 --> 00:10:47.580 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And it's
rarely shown to us.

00:10:47.580 --> 00:10:49.950 align:middle line:84%
We have to kind of weave
it together and pull

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:54.610 align:middle line:84%
from various experiences
and educational aspects

00:10:54.610 --> 00:10:55.410 align:middle line:90%
and components.

00:10:55.410 --> 00:10:56.730 align:middle line:90%
And we're the weaver.

00:10:56.730 --> 00:10:58.200 align:middle line:90%
And this, you know.

00:10:58.200 --> 00:11:00.330 align:middle line:84%
And I just want to
touch on something

00:11:00.330 --> 00:11:04.170 align:middle line:84%
that you mentioned
earlier about depression,

00:11:04.170 --> 00:11:06.558 align:middle line:84%
that while you're working
with these therapists

00:11:06.558 --> 00:11:08.850 align:middle line:84%
and therapists-to-be, and
they're coming to your dance,

00:11:08.850 --> 00:11:12.930 align:middle line:84%
and things are unfolding
and blossoming for them,

00:11:12.930 --> 00:11:15.540 align:middle line:84%
you mentioned something
special about depression

00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:19.650 align:middle line:84%
and how it wasn't present
for you, until it was.

00:11:19.650 --> 00:11:21.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Well, I
didn't know what

00:11:21.510 --> 00:11:24.240 align:middle line:84%
depression was
growing up, because I

00:11:24.240 --> 00:11:26.040 align:middle line:90%
hadn't seen anybody depressed.

00:11:26.040 --> 00:11:27.510 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah, this is amazing.

00:11:27.510 --> 00:11:31.630 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: In my community, I
hadn't seen anybody depressed.

00:11:31.630 --> 00:11:35.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think the first time I
heard about "nervous breakdown"

00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:38.782 align:middle line:84%
was in 1990 when I
went for a training

00:11:38.782 --> 00:11:39.740 align:middle line:90%
outside of the country.

00:11:39.740 --> 00:11:41.340 align:middle line:84%
And I said, what was
that "nervous breakdown"?

00:11:41.340 --> 00:11:42.270 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: What is a
"nervous breakdown"?

00:11:42.270 --> 00:11:44.590 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So they had
to explain it to me.

00:11:44.590 --> 00:11:49.440 align:middle line:84%
And I bet anyone who is
educated in psychology

00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:51.180 align:middle line:90%
would know these things.

00:11:51.180 --> 00:11:53.670 align:middle line:84%
But coming from my
background, I didn't

00:11:53.670 --> 00:11:57.560 align:middle line:84%
know anybody whose condition
was such that they would--

00:11:57.560 --> 00:11:59.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Would call
it depression-- why?

00:11:59.450 --> 00:12:02.040 align:middle line:90%
What do you attribute that to?

00:12:02.040 --> 00:12:05.130 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I think I grew up
in a communal environment,

00:12:05.130 --> 00:12:08.590 align:middle line:90%
where we lived together.

00:12:08.590 --> 00:12:14.560 align:middle line:84%
I grew up in a small house
with my mother and sisters

00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:19.350 align:middle line:84%
and all their children and other
extended family and other house

00:12:19.350 --> 00:12:20.150 align:middle line:90%
help.

00:12:20.150 --> 00:12:23.710 align:middle line:90%
We all lived in the small house.

00:12:23.710 --> 00:12:28.330 align:middle line:10%
And we played together,
we worked together,

00:12:28.330 --> 00:12:32.080 align:middle line:10%
we stood up for each other,
we looked out for each other

00:12:32.080 --> 00:12:34.180 align:middle line:10%
in our home.

00:12:34.180 --> 00:12:36.460 align:middle line:84%
But we will also
belong to the larger

00:12:36.460 --> 00:12:38.530 align:middle line:90%
community of other families.

00:12:38.530 --> 00:12:40.330 align:middle line:90%
And we played.

00:12:40.330 --> 00:12:45.070 align:middle line:84%
We would go away 10 miles,
8 miles away from home.

00:12:45.070 --> 00:12:47.200 align:middle line:90%
And I'm talking 10 years old.

00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:53.040 align:middle line:84%
We just were alive, playing,
making our own toys,

00:12:53.040 --> 00:12:58.440 align:middle line:84%
imagining games and connecting
with each other, fighting,

00:12:58.440 --> 00:13:02.527 align:middle line:84%
and all these natural
things children--

00:13:02.527 --> 00:13:04.485 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Just a real raw
expression and exchange.

00:13:04.485 --> 00:13:04.830 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:13:04.830 --> 00:13:05.830 align:middle line:90%
We were raw.

00:13:05.830 --> 00:13:06.630 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:13:06.630 --> 00:13:10.230 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: And one thing I found
in the years after was that

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:14.080 align:middle line:84%
those were some of the
best times of my life--

00:13:14.080 --> 00:13:19.890 align:middle line:84%
the challenge, the nurturing,
that sense of belonging--

00:13:19.890 --> 00:13:25.140 align:middle line:84%
actually, where the foundations
of who I have become.

00:13:25.140 --> 00:13:28.470 align:middle line:84%
Subsequently, we moved
from that environment

00:13:28.470 --> 00:13:34.500 align:middle line:84%
to another area that was more
comfortable, with more rooms

00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:37.950 align:middle line:90%
and bathrooms and everything.

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:42.210 align:middle line:84%
And that environment
also offered me some.

00:13:42.210 --> 00:13:48.270 align:middle line:84%
But I feel that all of
these living environments

00:13:48.270 --> 00:13:53.790 align:middle line:84%
contributed to my formation
in terms of who I have become.

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:55.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So it wasn't
that you didn't

00:13:55.890 --> 00:13:58.320 align:middle line:90%
experience challenging things.

00:13:58.320 --> 00:14:01.440 align:middle line:84%
But it was that your way of
processing the challenging

00:14:01.440 --> 00:14:05.100 align:middle line:84%
things that you were
experiencing was more communal.

00:14:05.100 --> 00:14:06.915 align:middle line:84%
You weren't an
isolated, separate self.

00:14:06.915 --> 00:14:07.915 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

00:14:07.915 --> 00:14:10.080 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: You were
networked and connected

00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:13.320 align:middle line:84%
into a larger body
of consciousness

00:14:13.320 --> 00:14:16.830 align:middle line:84%
or a larger body of people
that were in this collective.

00:14:16.830 --> 00:14:18.860 align:middle line:84%
This is what the healing
matrix is all about,

00:14:18.860 --> 00:14:21.763 align:middle line:84%
that we are wanting people
to realize they're not

00:14:21.763 --> 00:14:22.680 align:middle line:90%
a separate individual.

00:14:22.680 --> 00:14:25.350 align:middle line:84%
And to be present with
whatever they're experiencing

00:14:25.350 --> 00:14:27.610 align:middle line:90%
is the healer awakening.

00:14:27.610 --> 00:14:31.080 align:middle line:84%
And so you mentioned
that you've seen things

00:14:31.080 --> 00:14:35.040 align:middle line:84%
that were challenging, that
by the standards in the US,

00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:37.590 align:middle line:84%
for instance, you could have
been in a psych ward yourself.

00:14:37.590 --> 00:14:38.390 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: [LAUGHS]

00:14:38.390 --> 00:14:39.500 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Right.

00:14:39.500 --> 00:14:40.580 align:middle line:90%
But, no.

00:14:40.580 --> 00:14:42.120 align:middle line:90%
You've unfolded differently.

00:14:42.120 --> 00:14:43.980 align:middle line:90%
Can you just share about that?

00:14:43.980 --> 00:14:46.530 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: I was in grad school.

00:14:46.530 --> 00:14:49.710 align:middle line:90%
And they'll talk about trauma.

00:14:49.710 --> 00:14:54.830 align:middle line:84%
They'll talk about things
like bullying or name-calling.

00:14:54.830 --> 00:14:57.050 align:middle line:84%
All of those things
they talked about.

00:14:57.050 --> 00:15:03.500 align:middle line:84%
And apparently name-calling
can be damaging to a person,

00:15:03.500 --> 00:15:05.360 align:middle line:90%
irreparably.

00:15:05.360 --> 00:15:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, well,
if this was true,

00:15:09.170 --> 00:15:11.780 align:middle line:84%
then most of my
buddies from childhood

00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:14.800 align:middle line:90%
should be totally destroyed.

00:15:14.800 --> 00:15:21.810 align:middle line:84%
But I think how we
experience life has

00:15:21.810 --> 00:15:24.450 align:middle line:90%
something to do with culture.

00:15:24.450 --> 00:15:29.070 align:middle line:84%
Our expectations or
how we receive feedback

00:15:29.070 --> 00:15:33.860 align:middle line:84%
or experiences, it's not
isolated from a culture.

00:15:33.860 --> 00:15:36.350 align:middle line:84%
So within a certain
culture, a person

00:15:36.350 --> 00:15:43.280 align:middle line:84%
may be irreparably damaged
from name-calling or bullying

00:15:43.280 --> 00:15:45.440 align:middle line:90%
of any sort.

00:15:45.440 --> 00:15:49.370 align:middle line:90%
But for us, it was a raw world.

00:15:49.370 --> 00:15:52.800 align:middle line:84%
And I believe it
builds character.

00:15:52.800 --> 00:15:54.840 align:middle line:90%
It builds strength, resilience.

00:15:54.840 --> 00:15:58.740 align:middle line:84%
And also, when you
balance it with knowing

00:15:58.740 --> 00:16:01.650 align:middle line:84%
that you belong and there's
a sense of nurturance that

00:16:01.650 --> 00:16:06.210 align:middle line:84%
comes from your community,
it is a holistic environment

00:16:06.210 --> 00:16:10.740 align:middle line:84%
where challenge is just
one part of the whole.

00:16:10.740 --> 00:16:16.020 align:middle line:84%
But I guess for anyone who is
isolated and who feels lonely

00:16:16.020 --> 00:16:22.030 align:middle line:84%
or alone, a certain
experience may damage them.

00:16:22.030 --> 00:16:27.230 align:middle line:84%
So I'm interested in
that element of community

00:16:27.230 --> 00:16:30.950 align:middle line:84%
as a container for a
balanced development.

00:16:30.950 --> 00:16:32.090 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:16:32.090 --> 00:16:35.550 align:middle line:84%
In a healthy environment, that
challenge is the beginning.

00:16:35.550 --> 00:16:36.990 align:middle line:90%
It's not the end.

00:16:36.990 --> 00:16:39.230 align:middle line:84%
It's not the, close the
lid on the situation.

00:16:39.230 --> 00:16:42.380 align:middle line:84%
It's an impetus for us to become
creative, to find ourselves,

00:16:42.380 --> 00:16:44.840 align:middle line:84%
and to rise to that
creative tension,

00:16:44.840 --> 00:16:47.030 align:middle line:84%
if we're in a healthy
environment that

00:16:47.030 --> 00:16:50.810 align:middle line:84%
recognizes holism instead
of being victimized

00:16:50.810 --> 00:16:53.050 align:middle line:90%
by our circumstances.

00:16:53.050 --> 00:16:54.980 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I'd like to
speak of it this way.

00:16:54.980 --> 00:16:57.620 align:middle line:84%
I see all the
challenges that we face,

00:16:57.620 --> 00:16:59.670 align:middle line:90%
we could see them in two ways.

00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:03.170 align:middle line:84%
One way is see their
challenges as stumbling blocks.

00:17:03.170 --> 00:17:07.430 align:middle line:84%
But we can also see the same
challenges as stepping stones.

00:17:07.430 --> 00:17:10.010 align:middle line:84%
And how we see these
challenges depends

00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:12.829 align:middle line:84%
on our backgrounds, what
we believe about ourselves,

00:17:12.829 --> 00:17:15.079 align:middle line:90%
what environment we live in.

00:17:15.079 --> 00:17:20.760 align:middle line:84%
So I feel like a world
without challenges

00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:23.900 align:middle line:90%
would not be worth living.

00:17:23.900 --> 00:17:25.228 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Exactly.

00:17:25.228 --> 00:17:26.789 align:middle line:84%
It's what brings
the vital force.

00:17:26.789 --> 00:17:27.589 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:17:27.589 --> 00:17:28.835 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Allows us to
discover ourselves.

00:17:28.835 --> 00:17:29.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Mm-hmm, yeah.

00:17:29.810 --> 00:17:32.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And we have to begin
to learn to live with it

00:17:32.450 --> 00:17:35.390 align:middle line:84%
and learn from it and
awaken through it, rather

00:17:35.390 --> 00:17:37.700 align:middle line:90%
than being beaten down by it.

00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:39.800 align:middle line:90%
Now, you are an educated man.

00:17:39.800 --> 00:17:46.250 align:middle line:84%
You got your master's in
expressive arts and processing

00:17:46.250 --> 00:17:50.030 align:middle line:84%
traumas and experiences
differently.

00:17:50.030 --> 00:17:51.560 align:middle line:84%
What kind of research
were you being

00:17:51.560 --> 00:17:55.190 align:middle line:90%
provided in your education?

00:17:55.190 --> 00:17:57.830 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: At the time, I
realized there was a lot going

00:17:57.830 --> 00:18:02.090 align:middle line:84%
on regarding various
psychological models--

00:18:02.090 --> 00:18:06.620 align:middle line:84%
Freudian or humanistic
and all that energy work

00:18:06.620 --> 00:18:09.410 align:middle line:90%
and different modalities.

00:18:09.410 --> 00:18:13.010 align:middle line:84%
And, again, one thing
I noticed at the time

00:18:13.010 --> 00:18:20.920 align:middle line:84%
was that most of these
psychological models

00:18:20.920 --> 00:18:27.380 align:middle line:84%
were designed for fixing
problems, for healing.

00:18:27.380 --> 00:18:30.700 align:middle line:84%
But then I was looking at
things from the perspective

00:18:30.700 --> 00:18:35.170 align:middle line:84%
of my own experience
that the more I played,

00:18:35.170 --> 00:18:39.130 align:middle line:84%
the more I danced, the more
I felt connected to people.

00:18:39.130 --> 00:18:41.950 align:middle line:90%
To that extent, I felt strength.

00:18:41.950 --> 00:18:45.368 align:middle line:90%
And so this is one way I put it.

00:18:45.368 --> 00:18:52.860 align:middle line:84%
A person is at their best
when they've felt at home.

00:18:52.860 --> 00:18:54.540 align:middle line:84%
So wherever you
feel at home, you

00:18:54.540 --> 00:18:56.950 align:middle line:90%
are free to express yourself.

00:18:56.950 --> 00:18:58.430 align:middle line:90%
You are free to imagine.

00:18:58.430 --> 00:19:00.300 align:middle line:90%
You are free to create.

00:19:00.300 --> 00:19:04.650 align:middle line:84%
You are free to be your
full, authentic self.

00:19:04.650 --> 00:19:15.040 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm coming to this whole
realm of psychology and therapy

00:19:15.040 --> 00:19:19.150 align:middle line:84%
from a background
that emphasized

00:19:19.150 --> 00:19:20.990 align:middle line:90%
a sense of belonging.

00:19:20.990 --> 00:19:24.610 align:middle line:84%
Now that, put against
these psychological models,

00:19:24.610 --> 00:19:28.090 align:middle line:90%
sometimes seemed disparate.

00:19:28.090 --> 00:19:32.530 align:middle line:84%
And so what I was looking
at was, what can I

00:19:32.530 --> 00:19:36.410 align:middle line:90%
make of where I have come from?

00:19:36.410 --> 00:19:39.130 align:middle line:90%
Is there value to how I grew up?

00:19:39.130 --> 00:19:42.370 align:middle line:84%
Is there value to
my cultural ideals?

00:19:42.370 --> 00:19:46.820 align:middle line:84%
Is there value to the
cultural norms I grew up with?

00:19:46.820 --> 00:19:52.000 align:middle line:84%
And so the question I asked
was, if singing and dancing made

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:55.060 align:middle line:84%
me feel at home,
how could we tap

00:19:55.060 --> 00:19:58.240 align:middle line:90%
into that sense of comfort--

00:19:58.240 --> 00:20:01.110 align:middle line:84%
feeling comfortable
and in my element--

00:20:01.110 --> 00:20:06.400 align:middle line:84%
as a foundation for
facilitating human well-being.

00:20:06.400 --> 00:20:08.830 align:middle line:90%
So that's how I came into it.

00:20:08.830 --> 00:20:15.670 align:middle line:84%
So I was not particularly
interested in the ideas

00:20:15.670 --> 00:20:20.790 align:middle line:90%
regarding past lives or rebirth.

00:20:20.790 --> 00:20:25.090 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole practice
based on going back to your--

00:20:25.090 --> 00:20:25.890 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Regression.

00:20:25.890 --> 00:20:28.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Regression
therapy and all that.

00:20:28.620 --> 00:20:33.000 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, I'm sure there is
validity and legitimacy to all

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:33.930 align:middle line:90%
this.

00:20:33.930 --> 00:20:38.740 align:middle line:90%
But this is not my thing.

00:20:38.740 --> 00:20:44.440 align:middle line:84%
I am looking to reinvent
what I have known.

00:20:44.440 --> 00:20:48.380 align:middle line:84%
I'm looking to enhance
what I have known.

00:20:48.380 --> 00:20:53.930 align:middle line:84%
I'm looking to pushing the
edges of the evolution of what

00:20:53.930 --> 00:20:55.250 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:20:55.250 --> 00:20:59.090 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking at
dance from a perspective

00:20:59.090 --> 00:21:02.750 align:middle line:90%
that is cultural to me.

00:21:02.750 --> 00:21:07.250 align:middle line:84%
So for us, dance is
not just movement.

00:21:07.250 --> 00:21:10.220 align:middle line:10%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:21:10.220 --> 00:21:12.980 align:middle line:10%
Everything in the universe
is trying to evolve.

00:21:12.980 --> 00:21:15.830 align:middle line:90%
Everything is trying to expand.

00:21:15.830 --> 00:21:20.320 align:middle line:84%
The most important thing is
that you have an internal drive

00:21:20.320 --> 00:21:21.120 align:middle line:90%
for expansion.

00:21:21.120 --> 00:21:24.334 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:21:24.334 --> 00:21:27.268 align:middle line:90%


00:21:27.268 --> 00:21:30.210 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOPING]

00:21:30.210 --> 00:21:34.930 align:middle line:84%
When you start laughing at
yourself, nobody laughs at you.

00:21:34.930 --> 00:21:37.230 align:middle line:84%
Now, imagine that
you are not perfect

00:21:37.230 --> 00:21:39.420 align:middle line:90%
and you could never be perfect.

00:21:39.420 --> 00:21:41.460 align:middle line:84%
And if, because you
are not perfect,

00:21:41.460 --> 00:21:45.360 align:middle line:84%
you'll be pissed or sad or
depressed because you are not

00:21:45.360 --> 00:21:49.020 align:middle line:84%
perfect, how long will it
take you to get over it?

00:21:49.020 --> 00:21:51.330 align:middle line:84%
But when you embrace
where you are and you

00:21:51.330 --> 00:21:54.480 align:middle line:84%
face the right direction,
you are definitely

00:21:54.480 --> 00:21:56.280 align:middle line:90%
going to go in that direction.

00:21:56.280 --> 00:21:59.640 align:middle line:84%
But when you don't accept
it, you bring negative energy

00:21:59.640 --> 00:22:01.200 align:middle line:90%
and you go negative.

00:22:01.200 --> 00:22:04.470 align:middle line:84%
So always pretend you
are on your journey

00:22:04.470 --> 00:22:06.360 align:middle line:90%
and you know where you are.

00:22:06.360 --> 00:22:08.790 align:middle line:84%
And nobody can
make you feel bad.

00:22:08.790 --> 00:22:12.870 align:middle line:84%
That is the key to
daily experience

00:22:12.870 --> 00:22:15.570 align:middle line:90%
of joy and gratitude.

00:22:15.570 --> 00:22:19.860 align:middle line:84%
So every day, having
this feeling of gratitude

00:22:19.860 --> 00:22:23.640 align:middle line:84%
is the most richest
thing you can have.

00:22:23.640 --> 00:22:25.080 align:middle line:90%
It makes your face open.

00:22:25.080 --> 00:22:28.976 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:22:28.976 --> 00:22:32.385 align:middle line:90%
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

00:22:32.385 --> 00:22:36.770 align:middle line:90%


00:22:36.770 --> 00:22:39.470 align:middle line:90%
Dance is not just steps.

00:22:39.470 --> 00:22:43.550 align:middle line:84%
For us, dance is
intertwined with other art

00:22:43.550 --> 00:22:48.830 align:middle line:84%
forms, like music, poetry,
storytelling, costume, and all.

00:22:48.830 --> 00:22:53.010 align:middle line:84%
We work all these
into one context.

00:22:53.010 --> 00:22:54.010 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: A whole creation.

00:22:54.010 --> 00:22:55.093 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: A whole creation.

00:22:55.093 --> 00:22:58.990 align:middle line:84%
So for me, just moving
was not enough for me.

00:22:58.990 --> 00:23:04.060 align:middle line:84%
Just doing movement therapy
and somebody discern or infer

00:23:04.060 --> 00:23:08.770 align:middle line:84%
something about my past from
how I was moving was not--

00:23:08.770 --> 00:23:10.640 align:middle line:90%
I was thinking of rhythm.

00:23:10.640 --> 00:23:12.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking of
human connection.

00:23:12.700 --> 00:23:14.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm thinking of expression.

00:23:14.880 --> 00:23:15.833 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yes.

00:23:15.833 --> 00:23:17.250 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: And they're
transcendent.

00:23:17.250 --> 00:23:20.980 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking of all these
things within the context

00:23:20.980 --> 00:23:22.370 align:middle line:90%
of community.

00:23:22.370 --> 00:23:24.850 align:middle line:90%
So what does that leave me with?

00:23:24.850 --> 00:23:27.492 align:middle line:84%
Coming into a program
that was not--

00:23:27.492 --> 00:23:28.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: It didn't exist.

00:23:28.450 --> 00:23:29.860 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Didn't do that.

00:23:29.860 --> 00:23:31.330 align:middle line:90%
So I had to--

00:23:31.330 --> 00:23:32.170 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Create it.

00:23:32.170 --> 00:23:35.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So that would have
been a stumbling block for me.

00:23:35.410 --> 00:23:36.920 align:middle line:84%
But I used it as
a stepping stone--

00:23:36.920 --> 00:23:37.720 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Exactly.

00:23:37.720 --> 00:23:38.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --too.

00:23:38.520 --> 00:23:40.240 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: An example of--
exactly our point.

00:23:40.240 --> 00:23:41.087 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: [LAUGHS]

00:23:41.087 --> 00:23:42.670 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: You're saying,
it doesn't serve

00:23:42.670 --> 00:23:46.810 align:middle line:84%
us to continue to
find problems to fix,

00:23:46.810 --> 00:23:50.530 align:middle line:84%
because then all we ever do is
get good at fixing problems.

00:23:50.530 --> 00:23:53.180 align:middle line:84%
And we never really step
into our true artistry,

00:23:53.180 --> 00:23:53.980 align:middle line:90%
our creatorship.

00:23:53.980 --> 00:23:54.780 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Mm-hmm.

00:23:54.780 --> 00:23:56.910 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: We don't bloom into
our true purpose here.

00:23:56.910 --> 00:23:57.710 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:23:57.710 --> 00:24:01.930 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And so you had to find
and feel and express and allow

00:24:01.930 --> 00:24:05.650 align:middle line:84%
something new to be
merged from disciplines

00:24:05.650 --> 00:24:09.160 align:middle line:84%
that you were being trained to
this deep, core, soulful self

00:24:09.160 --> 00:24:11.950 align:middle line:84%
that was wanting to
rise up in an expression

00:24:11.950 --> 00:24:15.500 align:middle line:84%
and pierce into a modern
society with an ancient wisdom.

00:24:15.500 --> 00:24:16.300 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Mm-hmm.

00:24:16.300 --> 00:24:18.280 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And I'm so thrilled
that you're doing this.

00:24:18.280 --> 00:24:18.488 align:middle line:90%
It is--

00:24:18.488 --> 00:24:18.695 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah, thank you.

00:24:18.695 --> 00:24:21.190 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: --an amazing,
an amazing attribute

00:24:21.190 --> 00:24:23.720 align:middle line:90%
to do the context of healing.

00:24:23.720 --> 00:24:24.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:24:24.520 --> 00:24:26.312 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So you took it
in another direction.

00:24:26.312 --> 00:24:29.690 align:middle line:84%
What began to happen
as you did so?

00:24:29.690 --> 00:24:31.960 align:middle line:84%
What began to happen within
you or within the people

00:24:31.960 --> 00:24:33.910 align:middle line:84%
that you began to
share this with?

00:24:33.910 --> 00:24:36.010 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I think I
noticed early that I

00:24:36.010 --> 00:24:38.395 align:middle line:84%
couldn't fulfill all
the requirements to be

00:24:38.395 --> 00:24:40.480 align:middle line:90%
a licensed therapist.

00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:42.880 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't want to be that.

00:24:42.880 --> 00:24:50.250 align:middle line:84%
I realized my calling was more
for facilitating environments

00:24:50.250 --> 00:24:54.840 align:middle line:84%
where folks can dance,
can sing, can play,

00:24:54.840 --> 00:24:57.040 align:middle line:90%
can connect with each other.

00:24:57.040 --> 00:25:00.210 align:middle line:84%
And I found that I
had an advantage,

00:25:00.210 --> 00:25:05.730 align:middle line:84%
being that I could drum, I
could sing, I could dance,

00:25:05.730 --> 00:25:07.290 align:middle line:90%
I could tell stories.

00:25:07.290 --> 00:25:10.410 align:middle line:84%
And if I could pull
all of these together,

00:25:10.410 --> 00:25:12.900 align:middle line:90%
I could create a model--

00:25:12.900 --> 00:25:17.100 align:middle line:84%
a contemporary model--
that brings forth

00:25:17.100 --> 00:25:24.290 align:middle line:84%
the best from my culture,
coupled with other ideas

00:25:24.290 --> 00:25:28.350 align:middle line:84%
and stuff I have
learned along the way.

00:25:28.350 --> 00:25:33.980 align:middle line:84%
So I began to look at, how can
we do this traditional dance

00:25:33.980 --> 00:25:38.570 align:middle line:84%
in a way that actually makes
a difference in the lives

00:25:38.570 --> 00:25:41.090 align:middle line:90%
of the people in front of me?

00:25:41.090 --> 00:25:42.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So this
traditional dance,

00:25:42.610 --> 00:25:44.360 align:middle line:84%
are there certain
movements-- because it's

00:25:44.360 --> 00:25:45.450 align:middle line:90%
so beautiful to watch.

00:25:45.450 --> 00:25:48.650 align:middle line:90%
It's so vital and alive.

00:25:48.650 --> 00:25:52.280 align:middle line:84%
Is each movement a
piece of language?

00:25:52.280 --> 00:25:55.190 align:middle line:84%
Or is it organically
unfolding as a person

00:25:55.190 --> 00:25:59.460 align:middle line:84%
is expressing themselves in
an uninhibited, unplanned sort

00:25:59.460 --> 00:26:00.260 align:middle line:90%
of way?

00:26:00.260 --> 00:26:02.270 align:middle line:90%
What's happening here?

00:26:02.270 --> 00:26:05.620 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Well, first of
all, Africa is made up

00:26:05.620 --> 00:26:08.710 align:middle line:90%
of over 54 countries.

00:26:08.710 --> 00:26:13.150 align:middle line:84%
And each country has
many ethnic groups.

00:26:13.150 --> 00:26:18.520 align:middle line:84%
And each of these groups have
their own sets of dances.

00:26:18.520 --> 00:26:21.880 align:middle line:84%
These dances may be
social, recreational,

00:26:21.880 --> 00:26:23.740 align:middle line:90%
they may be religious.

00:26:23.740 --> 00:26:26.260 align:middle line:84%
They may be occupational,
meaning folks

00:26:26.260 --> 00:26:28.030 align:middle line:84%
in various occupations,
like fishermen

00:26:28.030 --> 00:26:34.180 align:middle line:84%
or hunters or blacksmiths will
have dances that they did.

00:26:34.180 --> 00:26:38.380 align:middle line:84%
But there'll be also dances
for worship and all sorts.

00:26:38.380 --> 00:26:41.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, given, for
example, that Ghana

00:26:41.440 --> 00:26:44.740 align:middle line:84%
has over 60 different
languages, you

00:26:44.740 --> 00:26:49.060 align:middle line:84%
can imagine the number of dances
that come out of Ghana alone.

00:26:49.060 --> 00:26:54.730 align:middle line:84%
So within each particular
group, the dances they do

00:26:54.730 --> 00:26:57.820 align:middle line:84%
may reflect something
about their history.

00:26:57.820 --> 00:26:59.800 align:middle line:84%
The dances they do
may reflect something

00:26:59.800 --> 00:27:02.950 align:middle line:90%
about the ideals and values.

00:27:02.950 --> 00:27:04.690 align:middle line:84%
The dances they do
may reflect something

00:27:04.690 --> 00:27:07.880 align:middle line:84%
about their environment
that they live in.

00:27:07.880 --> 00:27:09.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So they're
telling a story.

00:27:09.360 --> 00:27:10.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yep.

00:27:10.420 --> 00:27:14.020 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it's just
expression of joy.

00:27:14.020 --> 00:27:16.700 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it's an
expression of sadness,

00:27:16.700 --> 00:27:19.600 align:middle line:84%
because if you go to a funeral
and there's a funeral dance,

00:27:19.600 --> 00:27:23.050 align:middle line:84%
that dance fulfills
the aims and objectives

00:27:23.050 --> 00:27:25.900 align:middle line:90%
of the particular occasion.

00:27:25.900 --> 00:27:31.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, that given, in spite of the
diversity of cultures and dance

00:27:31.630 --> 00:27:32.440 align:middle line:90%
styles--

00:27:32.440 --> 00:27:34.870 align:middle line:84%
which means some
dances are softer,

00:27:34.870 --> 00:27:42.740 align:middle line:84%
some are more jump-oriented,
and some are more based

00:27:42.740 --> 00:27:46.210 align:middle line:90%
on the trunk or the torso--

00:27:46.210 --> 00:27:50.380 align:middle line:84%
now, in spite of that,
as Africans-- and I

00:27:50.380 --> 00:27:54.160 align:middle line:84%
will speak specifically
to sub-Saharan Africa,

00:27:54.160 --> 00:27:57.700 align:middle line:84%
we, have what we call
"shared aesthetics"

00:27:57.700 --> 00:28:01.390 align:middle line:84%
or shared sensibilities
in our dances.

00:28:01.390 --> 00:28:05.260 align:middle line:84%
So our dances tend
to be earthbound.

00:28:05.260 --> 00:28:06.932 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Mm, grounding.

00:28:06.932 --> 00:28:09.400 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Our movements
tend to be polycentric.

00:28:09.400 --> 00:28:11.890 align:middle line:84%
It means different parts of
the body doing different things

00:28:11.890 --> 00:28:12.690 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:28:12.690 --> 00:28:14.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Independently, mm-hmm.

00:28:14.470 --> 00:28:16.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: It means
we tend to dance

00:28:16.960 --> 00:28:21.560 align:middle line:84%
in a circle with the center
being the dance floor.

00:28:21.560 --> 00:28:25.840 align:middle line:84%
It means that audiences
participate with the dancers

00:28:25.840 --> 00:28:29.690 align:middle line:84%
by clapping or cheering
as the dance is going on.

00:28:29.690 --> 00:28:32.830 align:middle line:84%
There are several things that
are called commonalities.

00:28:32.830 --> 00:28:36.810 align:middle line:84%
And those are the things that
we can name as "African dance."

00:28:36.810 --> 00:28:41.080 align:middle line:84%
But that does not negate
the differences in style.

00:28:41.080 --> 00:28:46.360 align:middle line:84%
So in my work, I may draw
a specific dance from, say,

00:28:46.360 --> 00:28:49.600 align:middle line:84%
the Guang people of Ghana, or
I may draw a specific dance

00:28:49.600 --> 00:28:53.710 align:middle line:84%
from the Ewe people
of Ghana as an example

00:28:53.710 --> 00:28:59.230 align:middle line:84%
to address the larger
aesthetic of African dance.

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:03.720 align:middle line:84%
So while teaching
about African culture,

00:29:03.720 --> 00:29:08.540 align:middle line:84%
we are also looking at how
the students can become

00:29:08.540 --> 00:29:13.430 align:middle line:84%
the subjects or the
bodies that would

00:29:13.430 --> 00:29:18.410 align:middle line:84%
emulate their African values
that give birth to the dance.

00:29:18.410 --> 00:29:20.660 align:middle line:84%
So then we have to
create a community.

00:29:20.660 --> 00:29:24.390 align:middle line:84%
And as a community, we
have to work together.

00:29:24.390 --> 00:29:26.970 align:middle line:84%
And that is where it
goes to the personal.

00:29:26.970 --> 00:29:30.570 align:middle line:84%
So my work is
cultural, is community,

00:29:30.570 --> 00:29:31.988 align:middle line:90%
and is personal growth.

00:29:31.988 --> 00:29:33.780 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And therapeutic
because of all that.

00:29:33.780 --> 00:29:34.580 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:29:34.580 --> 00:29:39.240 align:middle line:84%
And personal means
engaging with the community

00:29:39.240 --> 00:29:41.020 align:middle line:90%
for the common good.

00:29:41.020 --> 00:29:45.340 align:middle line:84%
And that is the beginning
of self-awareness

00:29:45.340 --> 00:29:47.670 align:middle line:84%
that's the beginning of
understanding one's place

00:29:47.670 --> 00:29:48.690 align:middle line:90%
within--

00:29:48.690 --> 00:29:49.530 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Who I am in the world.

00:29:49.530 --> 00:29:49.920 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Who am I?

00:29:49.920 --> 00:29:50.490 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Who I am--

00:29:50.490 --> 00:29:50.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: in the universe?

00:29:50.590 --> 00:29:51.660 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: --in the world?

00:29:51.660 --> 00:29:56.970 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So the dance circle
or the context of the class

00:29:56.970 --> 00:30:01.080 align:middle line:90%
becomes, I call it, text.

00:30:01.080 --> 00:30:04.290 align:middle line:84%
Because if you are
literate, you can

00:30:04.290 --> 00:30:08.190 align:middle line:84%
read a lot of concepts
and philosophies

00:30:08.190 --> 00:30:10.050 align:middle line:90%
in the dance class.

00:30:10.050 --> 00:30:14.550 align:middle line:84%
As people are dancing,
certain dynamics speak.

00:30:14.550 --> 00:30:18.250 align:middle line:84%
So I talk about stepping stone
or stumble stumbling blocks.

00:30:18.250 --> 00:30:21.400 align:middle line:84%
You see somebody who
is about to give up--

00:30:21.400 --> 00:30:22.405 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Uh-huh.

00:30:22.405 --> 00:30:22.950 align:middle line:90%
Move.

00:30:22.950 --> 00:30:23.750 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:30:23.750 --> 00:30:28.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: How do we
name the options here?

00:30:28.410 --> 00:30:31.270 align:middle line:84%
You can give up or
you can step up.

00:30:31.270 --> 00:30:35.310 align:middle line:84%
So using the dance and the
songs and the relationships

00:30:35.310 --> 00:30:40.850 align:middle line:84%
as a context for drawing
awareness to the opportunity we

00:30:40.850 --> 00:30:42.110 align:middle line:90%
have.

00:30:42.110 --> 00:30:45.703 align:middle line:84%
That is where the
work becomes relevant.

00:30:45.703 --> 00:30:47.870 align:middle line:84%
So even though we are talking
about African culture,

00:30:47.870 --> 00:30:53.760 align:middle line:84%
we realize that it also speaks
to our actions and interactions

00:30:53.760 --> 00:30:54.560 align:middle line:90%
in the context.

00:30:54.560 --> 00:30:57.540 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And to everyone, in
real time, interculturally.

00:30:57.540 --> 00:30:58.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:30:58.340 --> 00:31:00.560 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Even if they've
never stepped foot in Africa

00:31:00.560 --> 00:31:02.090 align:middle line:84%
and they don't have
heritage there,

00:31:02.090 --> 00:31:03.680 align:middle line:90%
everyone benefits from this.

00:31:03.680 --> 00:31:08.240 align:middle line:84%
So tell me what happens
in the mind field.

00:31:08.240 --> 00:31:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I work with bioenergetics
and how the energy

00:31:10.100 --> 00:31:11.060 align:middle line:90%
flows through our body.

00:31:11.060 --> 00:31:12.860 align:middle line:84%
And the objective is
to keep the energy

00:31:12.860 --> 00:31:15.680 align:middle line:84%
moving through our body in
order for health and wholeness

00:31:15.680 --> 00:31:17.630 align:middle line:90%
and healing to be possible.

00:31:17.630 --> 00:31:21.170 align:middle line:84%
And so as you're getting
people to move and to engage,

00:31:21.170 --> 00:31:24.560 align:middle line:84%
can you just say a little bit
about what happens emotionally,

00:31:24.560 --> 00:31:27.440 align:middle line:84%
what happens to the physical
body, the emotional body,

00:31:27.440 --> 00:31:32.450 align:middle line:84%
the mind field, all collectively
when someone engages

00:31:32.450 --> 00:31:36.030 align:middle line:90%
in what you're stewarding here?

00:31:36.030 --> 00:31:38.390 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: That's a good question.

00:31:38.390 --> 00:31:41.410 align:middle line:84%
I think it's common knowledge
that physical activity does

00:31:41.410 --> 00:31:47.800 align:middle line:84%
a lot to enhance our well-being
in terms of releasing

00:31:47.800 --> 00:31:50.920 align:middle line:90%
certain chemicals in our body.

00:31:50.920 --> 00:31:54.730 align:middle line:84%
And we feel good when
we do physical activity.

00:31:54.730 --> 00:31:58.110 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things
that I say is this.

00:31:58.110 --> 00:32:02.470 align:middle line:84%
The human being is not
just a physical body, yeah?

00:32:02.470 --> 00:32:04.100 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Indeed.

00:32:04.100 --> 00:32:06.470 align:middle line:10%
>>SOWAH: The human
body is a network

00:32:06.470 --> 00:32:10.520 align:middle line:10%
of physical, emotional,
spiritual, psychological,

00:32:10.520 --> 00:32:13.400 align:middle line:10%
social, and all of that.

00:32:13.400 --> 00:32:16.310 align:middle line:84%
And so for me, just
physical movement

00:32:16.310 --> 00:32:22.280 align:middle line:90%
alone may not be the answer.

00:32:22.280 --> 00:32:23.080 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Can't be.

00:32:23.080 --> 00:32:24.380 align:middle line:90%
We're multidimensional.

00:32:24.380 --> 00:32:26.120 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: We are
multidimensional.

00:32:26.120 --> 00:32:30.680 align:middle line:84%
So just depending
on the physical act

00:32:30.680 --> 00:32:34.520 align:middle line:84%
of movement as the answer
is as good as thinking

00:32:34.520 --> 00:32:38.870 align:middle line:84%
you can just take vitamin
C and you'll be well.

00:32:38.870 --> 00:32:41.240 align:middle line:84%
The various vitamins
that your body needs

00:32:41.240 --> 00:32:43.130 align:middle line:90%
have to work together.

00:32:43.130 --> 00:32:49.950 align:middle line:84%
Some of these are responsible
for becoming the vehicles

00:32:49.950 --> 00:32:52.590 align:middle line:90%
for carrying other chemicals.

00:32:52.590 --> 00:32:57.120 align:middle line:84%
So they all need to be
meeting in the same place

00:32:57.120 --> 00:33:01.460 align:middle line:84%
at the right time to
affect functioning.

00:33:01.460 --> 00:33:02.660 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: The moving alchemist.

00:33:02.660 --> 00:33:03.460 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:33:03.460 --> 00:33:04.665 align:middle line:90%
So here we are.

00:33:04.665 --> 00:33:07.830 align:middle line:90%
We believe dance is healing.

00:33:07.830 --> 00:33:10.290 align:middle line:84%
I say dance has the
potential for healing.

00:33:10.290 --> 00:33:12.200 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Dance is the
potential for healing.

00:33:12.200 --> 00:33:12.750 align:middle line:90%
Movement is.

00:33:12.750 --> 00:33:13.890 align:middle line:10%
>>SOWAH: What that means--

00:33:13.890 --> 00:33:16.330 align:middle line:10%
movement has the
potential for healing.

00:33:16.330 --> 00:33:20.130 align:middle line:84%
But how do we create the
context, the environment,

00:33:20.130 --> 00:33:27.495 align:middle line:84%
and orchestrate a system that
allows various elements to come

00:33:27.495 --> 00:33:28.295 align:middle line:90%
together?

00:33:28.295 --> 00:33:34.290 align:middle line:84%
So I know many people who
have been destroyed by dance.

00:33:34.290 --> 00:33:36.980 align:middle line:84%
Sports is supposed
to be good for you.

00:33:36.980 --> 00:33:40.300 align:middle line:84%
I know many people who have
been destroyed by sports.

