giving, taking, sharing, asking

00:42:39.520 --> 00:42:42.010 align:middle line:84%
help, giving if
somebody in need,

00:42:42.010 --> 00:42:45.310 align:middle line:84%
taking responsibility, being
accountable-- all those things,

00:42:45.310 --> 00:42:47.560 align:middle line:90%
they build the whole person.

00:42:47.560 --> 00:42:52.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, in the process, the
fears and all the insecurities

00:42:52.440 --> 00:42:57.150 align:middle line:84%
are taken care of because
of that sense of belonging

00:42:57.150 --> 00:43:00.570 align:middle line:90%
and that authentic relationship.

00:43:00.570 --> 00:43:04.590 align:middle line:10%
And so people will say, these
are the best relationships

00:43:04.590 --> 00:43:08.460 align:middle line:10%
I've had in this university.

00:43:08.460 --> 00:43:11.400 align:middle line:84%
This is the first time I
have a real relationship.

00:43:11.400 --> 00:43:14.220 align:middle line:84%
Now, all these things
that people say

00:43:14.220 --> 00:43:24.100 align:middle line:84%
is a result of creating the
environment for life to unfold.

00:43:24.100 --> 00:43:29.720 align:middle line:10%
And a fully lived life is
physically therapeutic.

00:43:29.720 --> 00:43:30.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:43:30.520 --> 00:43:33.940 align:middle line:84%
What about this
power of intention?

00:43:33.940 --> 00:43:36.370 align:middle line:10%
What role does intention--
this ownership--

00:43:36.370 --> 00:43:39.280 align:middle line:10%
and you spoke about personal
responsibility-- what

00:43:39.280 --> 00:43:44.830 align:middle line:10%
can someone do to ensure that
as they're moving through dance,

00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:48.100 align:middle line:10%
as they're allowing themselves
to be a little bit more

00:43:48.100 --> 00:43:52.420 align:middle line:10%
physically mobile and allowing
those tissues to unwind

00:43:52.420 --> 00:43:55.280 align:middle line:10%
a bit and energies to
flow through their body,

00:43:55.280 --> 00:43:58.030 align:middle line:10%
what can they do with
their mind and their heart

00:43:58.030 --> 00:44:01.300 align:middle line:10%
in terms of intention and
personal responsibility

00:44:01.300 --> 00:44:04.840 align:middle line:10%
to ensure that it actually
has a therapeutic effect

00:44:04.840 --> 00:44:06.033 align:middle line:10%
in their life?

00:44:06.033 --> 00:44:08.200 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a difference
between just going out,

00:44:08.200 --> 00:44:08.710 align:middle line:90%
dancing--

00:44:08.710 --> 00:44:09.160 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: And dancing.

00:44:09.160 --> 00:44:11.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: --and dancing with the
true spirit and the awareness

00:44:11.890 --> 00:44:17.260 align:middle line:84%
and the embodiment of this
personally responsible

00:44:17.260 --> 00:44:21.370 align:middle line:84%
individual who gets and claims
that this is my life and I

00:44:21.370 --> 00:44:25.180 align:middle line:84%
get to be free and intentional
on these multiple dimensions

00:44:25.180 --> 00:44:26.110 align:middle line:90%
of my being.

00:44:26.110 --> 00:44:29.530 align:middle line:84%
What can you share to help
people ensure that they're

00:44:29.530 --> 00:44:32.680 align:middle line:84%
going to get the benefits
out of this movement

00:44:32.680 --> 00:44:34.680 align:middle line:90%
choice in their lives?

00:44:34.680 --> 00:44:37.330 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: There are many.

00:44:37.330 --> 00:44:41.960 align:middle line:84%
I think one is for
students to understand

00:44:41.960 --> 00:44:43.860 align:middle line:90%
the power of the will--

00:44:43.860 --> 00:44:44.660 align:middle line:90%
the will--

00:44:44.660 --> 00:44:45.460 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: The will.

00:44:45.460 --> 00:44:47.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --to will yourself.

00:44:47.590 --> 00:44:51.630 align:middle line:84%
Also understanding
that it is a journey.

00:44:51.630 --> 00:44:54.980 align:middle line:84%
I tell students,
this is not a sprint.

00:44:54.980 --> 00:44:56.740 align:middle line:90%
It's a marathon.

00:44:56.740 --> 00:45:00.790 align:middle line:90%
So don't expect to be perfect.

00:45:00.790 --> 00:45:03.070 align:middle line:84%
You may be an A student
in all your courses,

00:45:03.070 --> 00:45:09.430 align:middle line:84%
but in terms of somatic literacy
or somatic intelligence, you

00:45:09.430 --> 00:45:13.540 align:middle line:84%
may not be an adult.
You may be a baby.

00:45:13.540 --> 00:45:17.680 align:middle line:84%
So as a baby, you should have
baby expectations of yourself.

00:45:17.680 --> 00:45:19.400 align:middle line:90%
Be kind to yourself.

00:45:19.400 --> 00:45:23.650 align:middle line:84%
So I name all these things that
make people feel permission

00:45:23.650 --> 00:45:24.916 align:middle line:90%
to be where they are at.

00:45:24.916 --> 00:45:25.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Mm-hmm.

