00:45:29.920 --> 00:45:32.740 align:middle line:90%
What happens right there?

00:45:32.740 --> 00:45:34.920 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Self-acceptance.

00:45:34.920 --> 00:45:36.220 align:middle line:90%
Self-acceptance.

00:45:36.220 --> 00:45:39.420 align:middle line:84%
I tell students, I want you to
take this as a pillow fight.

00:45:39.420 --> 00:45:42.770 align:middle line:90%


00:45:42.770 --> 00:45:44.770 align:middle line:90%
I use that a lot.

00:45:44.770 --> 00:45:47.550 align:middle line:84%
When you are pillow
fighting, you

00:45:47.550 --> 00:45:49.642 align:middle line:84%
laugh whether you're
winning or losing.

00:45:49.642 --> 00:45:50.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: [LAUGHS] This is true.

00:45:50.850 --> 00:45:52.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: And you fight hard.

00:45:52.340 --> 00:45:53.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:45:53.140 --> 00:45:56.490 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: But your
self-esteem is not attached

00:45:56.490 --> 00:45:58.080 align:middle line:90%
to winning a pillow fight.

00:45:58.080 --> 00:45:59.610 align:middle line:90%
It's just play.

00:45:59.610 --> 00:46:05.610 align:middle line:84%
So I have students
begin to goof off.

00:46:05.610 --> 00:46:08.160 align:middle line:84%
So the whole first
week, few weeks of class

00:46:08.160 --> 00:46:13.710 align:middle line:84%
is what I call the
puppy dog phase--

00:46:13.710 --> 00:46:15.720 align:middle line:90%
pillow-fighting spirit.

00:46:15.720 --> 00:46:17.400 align:middle line:90%
So we sing silly songs.

00:46:17.400 --> 00:46:18.340 align:middle line:90%
We do silly movements.

00:46:18.340 --> 00:46:19.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Oh my gosh.

00:46:19.140 --> 00:46:23.610 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: And I require everybody
to get to know everybody.

00:46:23.610 --> 00:46:26.100 align:middle line:84%
Because to the extent to
which you know everyone,

00:46:26.100 --> 00:46:28.290 align:middle line:90%
to that extent you feel at home.

00:46:28.290 --> 00:46:30.420 align:middle line:84%
And when you feel at home,
you can pillow fight.

00:46:30.420 --> 00:46:31.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: You connect.

00:46:31.320 --> 00:46:33.990 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: If you don't
connect, you may not

00:46:33.990 --> 00:46:35.770 align:middle line:90%
be living your full life.

00:46:35.770 --> 00:46:38.700 align:middle line:84%
So in that process
of giving them

00:46:38.700 --> 00:46:42.660 align:middle line:84%
permission to do things they
can succeed at, like walking--

00:46:42.660 --> 00:46:47.520 align:middle line:84%
so I have students walk and
turn their walk into dance.

00:46:47.520 --> 00:46:49.940 align:middle line:84%
Now, that sense of success
gives some students

00:46:49.940 --> 00:46:52.950 align:middle line:84%
like, I didn't
know I could dance.

00:46:52.950 --> 00:46:53.940 align:middle line:90%
I just danced.

00:46:53.940 --> 00:46:54.240 align:middle line:90%
I just--

00:46:54.240 --> 00:46:55.642 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: [LAUGHS] I just did that.

00:46:55.642 --> 00:46:56.809 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: So it's just basic.

00:46:56.809 --> 00:46:59.010 align:middle line:84%
So how would you set
up a class to make

00:46:59.010 --> 00:47:02.915 align:middle line:84%
students feel successful
at every step of the way?

00:47:02.915 --> 00:47:04.290 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And then
what happens when

00:47:04.290 --> 00:47:07.980 align:middle line:84%
they dance with other
people differently than when

00:47:07.980 --> 00:47:10.110 align:middle line:90%
they just dance?

00:47:10.110 --> 00:47:13.210 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I think when you
dance with other people,

00:47:13.210 --> 00:47:15.090 align:middle line:84%
there's element of
being witnessed,

00:47:15.090 --> 00:47:21.660 align:middle line:84%
there's element of human
connection that is empowering.

00:47:21.660 --> 00:47:24.735 align:middle line:84%
And for many, they have
not experienced that.

00:47:24.735 --> 00:47:27.880 align:middle line:84%
There are people who
have evolved in dance,

00:47:27.880 --> 00:47:30.570 align:middle line:90%
but the dance is internal.

00:47:30.570 --> 00:47:33.110 align:middle line:84%
There's a place for
that kind of dance.

00:47:33.110 --> 00:47:40.360 align:middle line:84%
But when people begin
to dance in community,

00:47:40.360 --> 00:47:43.800 align:middle line:84%
it is different
because you are dancing

00:47:43.800 --> 00:47:47.420 align:middle line:84%
as a member of a
supportive community.

00:47:47.420 --> 00:47:50.580 align:middle line:84%
And it ceases to be
about just the movement.

00:47:50.580 --> 00:47:52.410 align:middle line:90%
It's a different experience.

00:47:52.410 --> 00:47:54.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Yes, so it's a
communion, it's an expression,

00:47:54.690 --> 00:47:56.640 align:middle line:84%
and it's a receptivity
at the same time.

00:47:56.640 --> 00:47:56.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yup.

00:47:56.850 --> 00:47:58.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: It's the
experience of oneness,

00:47:58.740 --> 00:48:00.370 align:middle line:90%
not the concept of oneness.

00:48:00.370 --> 00:48:01.170 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yup.

00:48:01.170 --> 00:48:03.630 align:middle line:84%
So I tell students, when
you stand in the circle

00:48:03.630 --> 00:48:05.400 align:middle line:84%
and somebody goes
to dance, I want

00:48:05.400 --> 00:48:09.150 align:middle line:84%
you to imagine this is
your two-year-old niece

00:48:09.150 --> 00:48:12.707 align:middle line:84%
or one-year-old nephew
who is trying to walk.

00:48:12.707 --> 00:48:13.840 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:48:13.840 --> 00:48:14.230 align:middle line:90%
You're encouraging.

00:48:14.230 --> 00:48:15.230 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: What do you do?

00:48:15.230 --> 00:48:20.500 align:middle line:84%
Make them walk, take another
step, or sit back down.

00:48:20.500 --> 00:48:23.280 align:middle line:90%
This is a community fire.

00:48:23.280 --> 00:48:25.950 align:middle line:90%
We all have to tend it.

00:48:25.950 --> 00:48:27.970 align:middle line:90%
So in this, it takes a village.

00:48:27.970 --> 00:48:29.510 align:middle line:90%
We practice it--

00:48:29.510 --> 00:48:30.570 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Beautiful.

00:48:30.570 --> 00:48:32.430 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --in the dance circle.

00:48:32.430 --> 00:48:35.130 align:middle line:84%
And people slowly
find their strength

00:48:35.130 --> 00:48:37.360 align:middle line:84%
and begin to believe
in themselves.

00:48:37.360 --> 00:48:41.520 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just the movement,
but it is the environment.

00:48:41.520 --> 00:48:45.900 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So they become
vulnerable and expressive

00:48:45.900 --> 00:48:48.460 align:middle line:84%
and then connected kind of
within seconds of each other.

00:48:48.460 --> 00:48:49.260 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes, yes.

00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:50.510 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: And that's the opening.

00:48:50.510 --> 00:48:52.950 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So the vulnerability
is the best weight.

00:48:52.950 --> 00:48:54.420 align:middle line:90%
How do you push through?

00:48:54.420 --> 00:48:58.660 align:middle line:84%
So we have songs we sing that
address each of these things.

00:48:58.660 --> 00:49:00.180 align:middle line:90%
For example, we have a chant.

00:49:00.180 --> 00:49:02.430 align:middle line:90%
We say, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:49:02.430 --> 00:49:20.400 align:middle line:90%


00:49:20.400 --> 00:49:21.960 align:middle line:84%
This is Pidgin
English from Ghana.

00:49:21.960 --> 00:49:25.690 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is
that, as a community member,

00:49:25.690 --> 00:49:28.020 align:middle line:90%
you get as much as you put in.

00:49:28.020 --> 00:49:30.220 align:middle line:90%
If you put--

00:49:30.220 --> 00:49:31.020 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: You reap.

00:49:31.020 --> 00:49:32.050 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --you reap.

00:49:32.050 --> 00:49:34.650 align:middle line:84%
And "chop" in Pidgin
English means "eat."

00:49:34.650 --> 00:49:37.960 align:middle line:84%
If you contribute, you get
to partake in the product.

00:49:37.960 --> 00:49:40.163 align:middle line:84%
But if you don't, it's
not going to happen.

00:49:40.163 --> 00:49:41.580 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: If you
don't, you're stuck.

00:49:41.580 --> 00:49:42.380 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

00:49:42.380 --> 00:49:45.270 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Now, you talk about
emotional constipation.

00:49:45.270 --> 00:49:49.440 align:middle line:84%
Is this one of the ways
that you would unpack that?

00:49:49.440 --> 00:49:50.790 align:middle line:90%
Describe this to us.

00:49:50.790 --> 00:49:53.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I like to
say that research

00:49:53.450 --> 00:49:55.690 align:middle line:84%
has shown that our
bodies are repositories

00:49:55.690 --> 00:49:59.310 align:middle line:84%
of our experiences, whether
physical experience,

00:49:59.310 --> 00:50:02.160 align:middle line:84%
emotional experience,
or our thoughts.

00:50:02.160 --> 00:50:04.590 align:middle line:84%
Our bodies are repositories
of our experiences.

00:50:04.590 --> 00:50:06.090 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: They hold
our unresolvedness.

00:50:06.090 --> 00:50:07.567 align:middle line:84%
The body holds
what's not resolved.

00:50:07.567 --> 00:50:08.550 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: They hold it.

00:50:08.550 --> 00:50:13.260 align:middle line:84%
And one thing we know
is that our bodies have

00:50:13.260 --> 00:50:15.900 align:middle line:90%
ways of recycling or purging.

00:50:15.900 --> 00:50:18.510 align:middle line:90%
So let's say you are hurt.

00:50:18.510 --> 00:50:20.280 align:middle line:90%
Something hits you.

00:50:20.280 --> 00:50:21.510 align:middle line:90%
You move.

00:50:21.510 --> 00:50:28.460 align:middle line:84%
And at the height of that
movement, you make a sound.

00:50:28.460 --> 00:50:31.440 align:middle line:90%
Or let's say you are happy.

00:50:31.440 --> 00:50:35.550 align:middle line:84%
You make a sound, and you
have a movement to go with it.

00:50:35.550 --> 00:50:37.680 align:middle line:84%
When you are in pain,
you make a sound

00:50:37.680 --> 00:50:39.990 align:middle line:84%
and you have a
movement to go with it.

00:50:39.990 --> 00:50:42.420 align:middle line:10%
When you are angry,
you make a sound

00:50:42.420 --> 00:50:45.463 align:middle line:10%
and you make a physical
motion to go with it.

00:50:45.463 --> 00:50:47.130 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: It doesn't get
to stop somewhere.

00:50:47.130 --> 00:50:47.743 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: It doesn't get to stop.

00:50:47.743 --> 00:50:48.300 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: You just keep it moving.

00:50:48.300 --> 00:50:49.670 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: It's flushing.

00:50:49.670 --> 00:50:49.776 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Got it.

00:50:49.776 --> 00:50:50.740 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: It's moving.

00:50:50.740 --> 00:50:56.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, we will live lives
where we inhibit expression,

00:50:56.340 --> 00:51:01.880 align:middle line:84%
whether vocal,
emotional, or physical,

00:51:01.880 --> 00:51:06.000 align:middle line:84%
where do we think
the energy goes?

00:51:06.000 --> 00:51:07.992 align:middle line:90%
I like to say this.

00:51:07.992 --> 00:51:11.830 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the body
needs you to yawn--

00:51:11.830 --> 00:51:12.740 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:51:12.740 --> 00:51:13.540 align:middle line:90%
And so it does.

00:51:13.540 --> 00:51:14.600 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --to flow.

00:51:14.600 --> 00:51:17.960 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes the body
needs you to sneeze.

00:51:17.960 --> 00:51:19.920 align:middle line:90%
And it does.

00:51:19.920 --> 00:51:22.260 align:middle line:10%
What happens when
you refuse to yawn?

00:51:22.260 --> 00:51:26.520 align:middle line:84%
What happens when
you refuse to sneeze?

00:51:26.520 --> 00:51:27.390 align:middle line:90%
What happens?

00:51:27.390 --> 00:51:33.770 align:middle line:84%
So if our body in our daily
experience is designed

00:51:33.770 --> 00:51:37.910 align:middle line:84%
to express what is going
on-- so you are happy,

00:51:37.910 --> 00:51:42.140 align:middle line:84%
you express joy physically;
you are angry, you express it;

00:51:42.140 --> 00:51:45.260 align:middle line:90%
you are happy, you express it--

00:51:45.260 --> 00:51:48.130 align:middle line:90%
expression is huge.

00:51:48.130 --> 00:51:53.810 align:middle line:84%
And movement is that
avenue for letting us

00:51:53.810 --> 00:51:56.540 align:middle line:90%
process our experiences fully.

00:51:56.540 --> 00:52:00.330 align:middle line:84%
Now, when we live in societies
where our movements are

00:52:00.330 --> 00:52:03.080 align:middle line:84%
curtailed, even our
voices are curtailed,

00:52:03.080 --> 00:52:06.110 align:middle line:84%
coming to African
dance and dancing,

00:52:06.110 --> 00:52:08.990 align:middle line:84%
coming to African
dance and singing,

00:52:08.990 --> 00:52:14.570 align:middle line:84%
coming to African dance and
expressing automatically taps

00:52:14.570 --> 00:52:17.380 align:middle line:84%
into various centers
of your being.

00:52:17.380 --> 00:52:20.100 align:middle line:84%
And it is not a thing that
can be put into words.

00:52:20.100 --> 00:52:22.400 align:middle line:84%
It's an experience
that people have.

00:52:22.400 --> 00:52:25.800 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it's
hard to articulate it.

00:52:25.800 --> 00:52:28.340 align:middle line:90%
But students know.

00:52:28.340 --> 00:52:31.310 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So just to be
clear for our viewers,

00:52:31.310 --> 00:52:34.580 align:middle line:84%
when that energy doesn't get
to go into full expression

00:52:34.580 --> 00:52:35.870 align:middle line:90%
and stay in motion--

00:52:35.870 --> 00:52:39.590 align:middle line:84%
make a sound, make a movement--
when it doesn't get to do that,

00:52:39.590 --> 00:52:40.673 align:middle line:90%
then what happens with it?

00:52:40.673 --> 00:52:41.882 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: That's constipation.

00:52:41.882 --> 00:52:43.390 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Where does the energy go?

00:52:43.390 --> 00:52:46.010 align:middle line:84%
And then how does this
emotional constipation

00:52:46.010 --> 00:52:50.240 align:middle line:84%
show up in people's physical
lives and their symptomatology?

00:52:50.240 --> 00:52:51.050 align:middle line:90%
What's the effect?

00:52:51.050 --> 00:52:53.150 align:middle line:84%
How are they going to
experience and know

00:52:53.150 --> 00:52:54.740 align:middle line:84%
that they are
emotionally constipated?

00:52:54.740 --> 00:52:55.940 align:middle line:84%
How are they going
to know that's what's

00:52:55.940 --> 00:52:56.740 align:middle line:90%
going on with them?

00:52:56.740 --> 00:53:03.080 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I cannot claim
to have any educated data

00:53:03.080 --> 00:53:07.470 align:middle line:84%
on the effects or the
lack of expression--

00:53:07.470 --> 00:53:08.650 align:middle line:90%
what it does to a person.

00:53:08.650 --> 00:53:11.132 align:middle line:90%


00:53:11.132 --> 00:53:12.840 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: But you can
share your experience,

00:53:12.840 --> 00:53:13.630 align:middle line:90%
what you've observed.

00:53:13.630 --> 00:53:14.630 align:middle line:90%
That's all we're asking.

00:53:14.630 --> 00:53:17.590 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: We know
that some students,

00:53:17.590 --> 00:53:21.730 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of class, will
feel a huge wave of emotion.

00:53:21.730 --> 00:53:24.580 align:middle line:90%
And they will just break down.

00:53:24.580 --> 00:53:26.920 align:middle line:90%
Some students might shake.

00:53:26.920 --> 00:53:33.088 align:middle line:10%
Some students might have "aha"
moments through the movement.

00:53:33.088 --> 00:53:34.130 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: As it's releasing.

00:53:34.130 --> 00:53:35.630 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: As it releases.

00:53:35.630 --> 00:53:42.360 align:middle line:10%
And I think it's important
to look at our society,

00:53:42.360 --> 00:53:45.120 align:middle line:10%
to see the levels
of, let's say, cancer

00:53:45.120 --> 00:53:50.760 align:middle line:10%
or depression or
physical inhibitions

00:53:50.760 --> 00:53:52.980 align:middle line:10%
and how people
hold their bodies,

00:53:52.980 --> 00:54:02.130 align:middle line:10%
and connect that to the
individuals' lifestyle--

00:54:02.130 --> 00:54:06.400 align:middle line:10%
what they do, the
kinds of communities

00:54:06.400 --> 00:54:09.970 align:middle line:10%
they walk in, or lack
thereof they walk in.

00:54:09.970 --> 00:54:15.550 align:middle line:84%
Our bodies reflect our
lifestyles and our values

00:54:15.550 --> 00:54:16.910 align:middle line:90%
and our activities.

00:54:16.910 --> 00:54:19.690 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So you're saying that
this emotional constipation not

00:54:19.690 --> 00:54:22.180 align:middle line:84%
expressing could
lead to the things

00:54:22.180 --> 00:54:24.050 align:middle line:84%
that we consider our
disease processes.

00:54:24.050 --> 00:54:24.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Diseases.

00:54:24.850 --> 00:54:27.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Headaches, back
pain, indigestion, asthma,

00:54:27.410 --> 00:54:29.500 align:middle line:84%
allergies-- all of it has
to do with stuck energy.

00:54:29.500 --> 00:54:30.300 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:54:30.300 --> 00:54:32.020 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Stuck emotional energy.

00:54:32.020 --> 00:54:32.820 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Energy.

00:54:32.820 --> 00:54:36.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And now you're saying
also that when we engage

00:54:36.520 --> 00:54:39.190 align:middle line:90%
in a community that is aware--

00:54:39.190 --> 00:54:40.485 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Aware and supportive.

00:54:40.485 --> 00:54:43.810 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: --and supportive that
this energy automatically

00:54:43.810 --> 00:54:45.310 align:middle line:90%
starts flowing.

00:54:45.310 --> 00:54:47.790 align:middle line:84%
It gets drawn up and out of
us, that which has been stuck--

00:54:47.790 --> 00:54:48.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Stuck.

00:54:48.590 --> 00:54:49.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: --et cetera.

00:54:49.140 --> 00:54:49.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

00:54:49.420 --> 00:54:52.360 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So when people don't have
a community surrounding them,

00:54:52.360 --> 00:54:53.470 align:middle line:90%
what can they do?

00:54:53.470 --> 00:54:59.410 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Well, up until now,
we have dependent on medication

00:54:59.410 --> 00:55:01.640 align:middle line:90%
to numb things.

00:55:01.640 --> 00:55:02.440 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:55:02.440 --> 00:55:04.226 align:middle line:84%
Well, those days
are numbered, right?

00:55:04.226 --> 00:55:04.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: They are.

00:55:04.480 --> 00:55:05.250 align:middle line:90%
Yup.

00:55:05.250 --> 00:55:06.417 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: People are waking up.

00:55:06.417 --> 00:55:08.380 align:middle line:90%
There's got to be another way.

00:55:08.380 --> 00:55:11.860 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: By now, we know
that the allopathic is not

00:55:11.860 --> 00:55:12.660 align:middle line:90%
the answer to all.

00:55:12.660 --> 00:55:13.868 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Not the whole picture.

00:55:13.868 --> 00:55:16.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: There is a place
for allopathic medicine.

00:55:16.180 --> 00:55:16.980 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

00:55:16.980 --> 00:55:20.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: And what we
are saying is this.

00:55:20.450 --> 00:55:25.330 align:middle line:84%
As human beings, we
are wired to express.

00:55:25.330 --> 00:55:26.830 align:middle line:90%
We are wired to move.

00:55:26.830 --> 00:55:29.050 align:middle line:90%
We are wired to connect.

00:55:29.050 --> 00:55:33.000 align:middle line:84%
And when we stop those
things, inhibit those things,

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:34.630 align:middle line:90%
there are consequences.

00:55:34.630 --> 00:55:42.540 align:middle line:84%
And the solution is not to
band-aid the consequences,

00:55:42.540 --> 00:55:46.530 align:middle line:84%
but to rethink what
we call "normal life,"

00:55:46.530 --> 00:55:51.540 align:middle line:84%
to think what we call a normal
way of being in relationships,

00:55:51.540 --> 00:55:54.710 align:middle line:84%
and ask ourselves, are we
going in the right direction?

00:55:54.710 --> 00:55:58.920 align:middle line:84%
Or do we need to recalibrate
our, what we call,

00:55:58.920 --> 00:56:00.870 align:middle line:84%
"decent," what we
call "respectable,"

00:56:00.870 --> 00:56:03.240 align:middle line:90%
what we call "normal"?

00:56:03.240 --> 00:56:08.160 align:middle line:84%
And so what we do in class
is just that-- questioning

00:56:08.160 --> 00:56:11.520 align:middle line:90%
what people consider normal.

00:56:11.520 --> 00:56:15.410 align:middle line:84%
And as a human society,
the question I ask

00:56:15.410 --> 00:56:18.120 align:middle line:84%
is, when we talk
about innovation,

00:56:18.120 --> 00:56:20.880 align:middle line:84%
we have made
innovations in machines.

00:56:20.880 --> 00:56:24.450 align:middle line:84%
We have made innovations
in all sorts of ways.

00:56:24.450 --> 00:56:29.220 align:middle line:84%
So we don't use iPhone
4 as much as we used to.

00:56:29.220 --> 00:56:30.960 align:middle line:90%
We are now at iPhone 10.

00:56:30.960 --> 00:56:36.540 align:middle line:84%
As humans, how much do we
invest in rethinking our--

00:56:36.540 --> 00:56:37.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Internal world.

00:56:37.470 --> 00:56:41.010 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: --our internal
world, our social constructs

00:56:41.010 --> 00:56:43.255 align:middle line:90%
of reality, our spiritual--

00:56:43.255 --> 00:56:44.130 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: The invisible.

00:56:44.130 --> 00:56:45.510 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --the invisible.

00:56:45.510 --> 00:56:50.640 align:middle line:84%
Are we looking at ways
to upgrade the human?

00:56:50.640 --> 00:56:51.550 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yes.

00:56:51.550 --> 00:56:55.590 align:middle line:10%
You speak about dance
being a human right.

00:56:55.590 --> 00:56:57.735 align:middle line:10%
Can you elaborate
on that for us?

00:56:57.735 --> 00:57:00.930 align:middle line:10%
>>SOWAH: Well,
there's no saying.

00:57:00.930 --> 00:57:04.410 align:middle line:90%
Every human society has dance.

00:57:04.410 --> 00:57:08.610 align:middle line:84%
And I know from
research that Europeans

00:57:08.610 --> 00:57:15.300 align:middle line:84%
used to dance ecstatic dances
and wild dances, human dances.

00:57:15.300 --> 00:57:18.990 align:middle line:84%
But at some point, with
the Puritanic movement,

00:57:18.990 --> 00:57:20.350 align:middle line:90%
all these things were--

00:57:20.350 --> 00:57:21.150 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Shut down.

00:57:21.150 --> 00:57:22.170 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --shut down.

00:57:22.170 --> 00:57:24.370 align:middle line:90%
Now we have consequences.

00:57:24.370 --> 00:57:25.170 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:57:25.170 --> 00:57:30.060 align:middle line:84%
So basically, my case for the
need for everyone to dance

00:57:30.060 --> 00:57:36.780 align:middle line:84%
has something to do with, one,
the movement, two, rhythm,

00:57:36.780 --> 00:57:39.870 align:middle line:90%
three, in community.

00:57:39.870 --> 00:57:42.420 align:middle line:84%
And they transcended
into the spirit.

00:57:42.420 --> 00:57:49.080 align:middle line:84%
All of these are necessary
for the full benefit of dance.

00:57:49.080 --> 00:57:52.560 align:middle line:84%
I like to see dance I
say like a landscape.

00:57:52.560 --> 00:57:55.860 align:middle line:84%
When you look out in the
window, you see the mountains.

00:57:55.860 --> 00:57:57.270 align:middle line:90%
They're beautiful.

00:57:57.270 --> 00:57:58.740 align:middle line:90%
We can groom the mountain.

00:57:58.740 --> 00:58:02.940 align:middle line:84%
We can groom the forest
to look beautiful.

00:58:02.940 --> 00:58:06.900 align:middle line:84%
But to think that the purpose
of the forest or the landscape

00:58:06.900 --> 00:58:11.550 align:middle line:84%
is just for beauty
is a little wanting

00:58:11.550 --> 00:58:17.260 align:middle line:84%
because we know that the forest
has more to offer humanity

00:58:17.260 --> 00:58:18.237 align:middle line:90%
than just pretty.

00:58:18.237 --> 00:58:19.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Than meets the eye.

00:58:19.320 --> 00:58:19.680 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Meets the eye.

00:58:19.680 --> 00:58:20.972 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: More than meets the eye.

00:58:20.972 --> 00:58:23.700 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: In the same way,
much as I appreciate art,

00:58:23.700 --> 00:58:29.130 align:middle line:84%
I appreciate aesthetic
of movement or music,

00:58:29.130 --> 00:58:35.600 align:middle line:84%
I know these human phenomena
are not only for beauty.

00:58:35.600 --> 00:58:38.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: There is a wave and
a pulsation to the whole

00:58:38.960 --> 00:58:40.010 align:middle line:90%
of the manifest world.

00:58:40.010 --> 00:58:42.210 align:middle line:90%
All of creation is moving.

00:58:42.210 --> 00:58:44.780 align:middle line:84%
The constellations are
moving, the planetary orbits,

00:58:44.780 --> 00:58:47.638 align:middle line:84%
the continual wave
motion of our oceans

00:58:47.638 --> 00:58:48.680 align:middle line:90%
and the winds, et cetera.

00:58:48.680 --> 00:58:50.930 align:middle line:90%
Everything is in movement.

00:58:50.930 --> 00:58:56.270 align:middle line:84%
And so when we as human beings
start to clamp down on our life

00:58:56.270 --> 00:58:59.720 align:middle line:84%
experience and we carry
stress and we carry stiffness

00:58:59.720 --> 00:59:06.770 align:middle line:84%
and rigidity, is this movement
within the human bandwidth

00:59:06.770 --> 00:59:08.210 align:middle line:90%
becoming extinct?

00:59:08.210 --> 00:59:10.430 align:middle line:84%
Are we shutting it
down to the point

00:59:10.430 --> 00:59:14.120 align:middle line:84%
that there will be
tremendous effect?

00:59:14.120 --> 00:59:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And if so, what
effects do you see?

00:59:16.730 --> 00:59:19.340 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Here's I see it.

00:59:19.340 --> 00:59:25.130 align:middle line:84%
I feel that as human beings,
we are daily evolving.

00:59:25.130 --> 00:59:27.860 align:middle line:90%
We are daily transforming.

00:59:27.860 --> 00:59:30.900 align:middle line:84%
The question is, which
direction are we going?

00:59:30.900 --> 00:59:35.190 align:middle line:84%
Because every day,
our lives are impacted

00:59:35.190 --> 00:59:38.460 align:middle line:84%
by what we see, what
we smell, what we hear.

00:59:38.460 --> 00:59:43.650 align:middle line:84%
Our diet determines
what direction we go.

00:59:43.650 --> 00:59:48.180 align:middle line:84%
And what I say is that
we have natural systems.

00:59:48.180 --> 00:59:54.130 align:middle line:10%
And some of these natural
systems do not change.

00:59:54.130 --> 00:59:58.420 align:middle line:84%
For example, our bodies
are wired to be used.

00:59:58.420 --> 01:00:04.060 align:middle line:84%
If we don't use it, certain
parts of our brains get toast.

01:00:04.060 --> 01:00:10.280 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] Certain parts of
our brains are reduced to--

01:00:10.280 --> 01:00:11.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: They go dormant.

01:00:11.520 --> 01:00:11.680 align:middle line:90%
Shut down.

01:00:11.680 --> 01:00:12.730 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: --dormancy.

01:00:12.730 --> 01:00:15.120 align:middle line:90%
So the question is this.

01:00:15.120 --> 01:00:18.160 align:middle line:84%
In our development,
where we have

01:00:18.160 --> 01:00:21.880 align:middle line:84%
so much material
and external stuff,

01:00:21.880 --> 01:00:25.890 align:middle line:84%
what price are we
paying internally?

01:00:25.890 --> 01:00:31.650 align:middle line:84%
The human being is upright
and functioning, I say,

01:00:31.650 --> 01:00:34.060 align:middle line:90%
because of polyrhythm.

01:00:34.060 --> 01:00:37.710 align:middle line:84%
There is brain function,
movement, there's heart,

01:00:37.710 --> 01:00:43.410 align:middle line:84%
there is lungs, there is
ribs, there is peristalsis.

01:00:43.410 --> 01:00:45.330 align:middle line:84%
There's so much
movement in the body.

01:00:45.330 --> 01:00:49.620 align:middle line:84%
Even within the heart, there's
so much rhythm in there.

01:00:49.620 --> 01:00:53.910 align:middle line:84%
And every part of the
body works in its own way

01:00:53.910 --> 01:00:58.170 align:middle line:84%
to contribute to
the common good.

01:00:58.170 --> 01:01:04.590 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: And as we begin to tap
in to this polyrhythmic reality

01:01:04.590 --> 01:01:08.580 align:middle line:84%
that we are, what is our
greatest asset that we can

01:01:08.580 --> 01:01:11.500 align:middle line:84%
offer to a society
that is disconnected,

01:01:11.500 --> 01:01:13.610 align:middle line:84%
that is not well, that is
not in their wholeness,

01:01:13.610 --> 01:01:16.695 align:middle line:84%
and we would
consider sick or ill?

01:01:16.695 --> 01:01:21.540 align:middle line:84%
What can we offer once we
connect our multiplicity

01:01:21.540 --> 01:01:26.340 align:middle line:84%
into a unified, empowered,
soulful individual?

01:01:26.340 --> 01:01:28.870 align:middle line:90%
What happens there?

01:01:28.870 --> 01:01:36.630 align:middle line:10%
>>SOWAH: I think when I would
talk to folks about healing,

01:01:36.630 --> 01:01:42.150 align:middle line:10%
many people tend to focus
on healing for themselves.

01:01:42.150 --> 01:01:47.030 align:middle line:84%
But I think we find our
healing in the context

01:01:47.030 --> 01:01:51.290 align:middle line:84%
of our interdependence
in our relationships.

01:01:51.290 --> 01:01:55.820 align:middle line:90%
It's like a matrix of healing.

01:01:55.820 --> 01:02:02.430 align:middle line:84%
In other words, as I
give of my best to you,

01:02:02.430 --> 01:02:05.070 align:middle line:90%
I receive what I need.

01:02:05.070 --> 01:02:11.980 align:middle line:84%
And I think, as a society,
we are losing that lens

01:02:11.980 --> 01:02:15.880 align:middle line:84%
in terms of seeing how
our wellness depends

01:02:15.880 --> 01:02:18.050 align:middle line:90%
on the wellness of others.

01:02:18.050 --> 01:02:23.680 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So in this healing
matrix that you're referencing,

01:02:23.680 --> 01:02:26.590 align:middle line:84%
we're perceiving ourselves
as a bigger being.

01:02:26.590 --> 01:02:30.100 align:middle line:84%
We're interconnected to the
point that they belong to us,

01:02:30.100 --> 01:02:31.000 align:middle line:90%
we belong to them.

01:02:31.000 --> 01:02:32.840 align:middle line:90%
There is no other.

01:02:32.840 --> 01:02:34.030 align:middle line:90%
It's a bigger being.

01:02:34.030 --> 01:02:36.490 align:middle line:84%
So we're thinking too
small when it's me,

01:02:36.490 --> 01:02:38.290 align:middle line:84%
me, me, and we're
trying to heal.

01:02:38.290 --> 01:02:40.720 align:middle line:84%
The reason we don't heal
when it's a me, me, me,

01:02:40.720 --> 01:02:42.790 align:middle line:84%
is that we're isolating
and thinking too small.

01:02:42.790 --> 01:02:45.190 align:middle line:90%
So you're saying, let's expand.

01:02:45.190 --> 01:02:46.450 align:middle line:90%
Let's open up.

01:02:46.450 --> 01:02:50.110 align:middle line:90%
Let's allow communion in this.

01:02:50.110 --> 01:02:52.650 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: I see it this way.

01:02:52.650 --> 01:02:56.610 align:middle line:84%
When you tend to think
just about yourself,

01:02:56.610 --> 01:02:59.670 align:middle line:84%
sometimes you have a
tape of self-doubt--

01:02:59.670 --> 01:03:04.900 align:middle line:84%
tape of self-criticism,
a tape of imperfection.

01:03:04.900 --> 01:03:06.630 align:middle line:84%
But the moment
you begin to think

01:03:06.630 --> 01:03:08.460 align:middle line:84%
of others, their
well-being, you're

01:03:08.460 --> 01:03:11.250 align:middle line:90%
not focusing on yourself.

01:03:11.250 --> 01:03:15.600 align:middle line:84%
You begin to participate
in the common good.

01:03:15.600 --> 01:03:19.280 align:middle line:84%
And then, that sense
of fulfillment,

01:03:19.280 --> 01:03:21.980 align:middle line:84%
that sense of purpose,
when you begin

01:03:21.980 --> 01:03:27.800 align:middle line:84%
to play your part in the
whole, that sense of purpose

01:03:27.800 --> 01:03:29.330 align:middle line:90%
is the root of healing.

01:03:29.330 --> 01:03:30.380 align:middle line:90%
It's empowering.

01:03:30.380 --> 01:03:37.290 align:middle line:10%
It's life-giving when you begin
to find your purpose in life.

01:03:37.290 --> 01:03:40.020 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: In that self-doubt
in the "me, me, me,"

01:03:40.020 --> 01:03:44.650 align:middle line:84%
focus, what happens is, we
feel like something is missing.

01:03:44.650 --> 01:03:47.340 align:middle line:84%
And so we start running the mind
and writing a story about what

01:03:47.340 --> 01:03:48.487 align:middle line:90%
it could possibly be--

01:03:48.487 --> 01:03:50.820 align:middle line:84%
well, I'm not enough of this,
or I'm not enough of that,

01:03:50.820 --> 01:03:52.020 align:middle line:90%
or I compare myself--

01:03:52.020 --> 01:03:55.070 align:middle line:84%
all because there's a sense
that something is missing.

01:03:55.070 --> 01:03:56.880 align:middle line:84%
And what you're
saying is missing

01:03:56.880 --> 01:04:00.900 align:middle line:84%
is our realization that
there's a larger organism here

01:04:00.900 --> 01:04:02.370 align:middle line:90%
that we call community.

01:04:02.370 --> 01:04:05.730 align:middle line:84%
And the moment I start
thinking of others, too,

01:04:05.730 --> 01:04:08.940 align:middle line:84%
I include myself in
that larger organism.

01:04:08.940 --> 01:04:11.970 align:middle line:84%
And so I feel a greater
sense of fulfillment

01:04:11.970 --> 01:04:14.820 align:middle line:84%
because I'm allowing
more energies,

01:04:14.820 --> 01:04:18.340 align:middle line:84%
more diversity to be a
part of my personal world

01:04:18.340 --> 01:04:19.680 align:middle line:90%
and my personal identity.

01:04:19.680 --> 01:04:20.090 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

01:04:20.090 --> 01:04:20.480 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yes?

01:04:20.480 --> 01:04:20.770 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yes.

01:04:20.770 --> 01:04:22.437 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: That's where
the healing happens.

01:04:22.437 --> 01:04:25.580 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So you become
part of a bigger energy.

01:04:25.580 --> 01:04:29.160 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
I do a lot in my work

01:04:29.160 --> 01:04:31.090 align:middle line:90%
is naming these things as we go.

01:04:31.090 --> 01:04:35.480 align:middle line:84%
So if somebody comes
in the circle to dance,

01:04:35.480 --> 01:04:40.230 align:middle line:84%
it is not for you to
judge them or think

01:04:40.230 --> 01:04:42.250 align:middle line:90%
how you're going to beat them.

01:04:42.250 --> 01:04:45.673 align:middle line:84%
Your job is to make them
be the best they could be.

01:04:45.673 --> 01:04:46.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Celebrate them.

01:04:46.590 --> 01:04:47.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Celebrate them.

01:04:47.850 --> 01:04:51.460 align:middle line:84%
And then when you come
in, no matter who you are,

01:04:51.460 --> 01:04:53.100 align:middle line:90%
people celebrate you.

01:04:53.100 --> 01:04:56.960 align:middle line:84%
And when we create that
society, then we'll

01:04:56.960 --> 01:05:00.260 align:middle line:84%
be heading somewhere-- a
society where we look out

01:05:00.260 --> 01:05:02.880 align:middle line:90%
for the best in each other.

01:05:02.880 --> 01:05:05.450 align:middle line:90%
We look out for the best.

01:05:05.450 --> 01:05:09.590 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Can you speak
about restoring harmony

01:05:09.590 --> 01:05:14.010 align:middle line:84%
within the individual in
order to heal relationships?

01:05:14.010 --> 01:05:16.848 align:middle line:90%
Restoring harmony.

01:05:16.848 --> 01:05:17.732 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: [SCOFFS]

01:05:17.732 --> 01:05:18.620 align:middle line:90%


01:05:18.620 --> 01:05:26.840 align:middle line:84%
I think that we are
all works in progress.

01:05:26.840 --> 01:05:28.925 align:middle line:90%
And I said it before--

01:05:28.925 --> 01:05:31.650 align:middle line:90%
self-acceptance is huge.

01:05:31.650 --> 01:05:34.790 align:middle line:10%
So one metaphor I
use a lot in my work

01:05:34.790 --> 01:05:42.210 align:middle line:10%
is that of the making
of the butterfly.

01:05:42.210 --> 01:05:43.650 align:middle line:10%
When you see the
cocoon, when you

01:05:43.650 --> 01:05:48.780 align:middle line:10%
see the various stages
of the butterfly, or even

01:05:48.780 --> 01:05:50.235 align:middle line:10%
when you see a plant--

01:05:50.235 --> 01:05:52.890 align:middle line:10%
a bud grow into a flower--

01:05:52.890 --> 01:05:56.030 align:middle line:10%
it starts like this.

01:05:56.030 --> 01:06:01.530 align:middle line:84%
Everything in that
plant is pushing.

01:06:01.530 --> 01:06:03.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Rise.

01:06:03.450 --> 01:06:04.750 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: That is our job.

01:06:04.750 --> 01:06:07.770 align:middle line:84%
So when you feel the need to
push, when you have challenges,

01:06:07.770 --> 01:06:09.660 align:middle line:90%
it's not the end.

01:06:09.660 --> 01:06:14.190 align:middle line:84%
That push is
necessary to come out

01:06:14.190 --> 01:06:16.830 align:middle line:90%
with wings that will not fall.

01:06:16.830 --> 01:06:21.600 align:middle line:84%
That push is necessary to
build the necessary strength

01:06:21.600 --> 01:06:23.130 align:middle line:90%
to face the world.

01:06:23.130 --> 01:06:26.760 align:middle line:84%
And so I tell the students, when
you feel the challenge, that

01:06:26.760 --> 01:06:28.620 align:middle line:90%
is where the medicine is.

01:06:28.620 --> 01:06:36.610 align:middle line:10%
Now, accepting that each part
belongs in the larger picture

01:06:36.610 --> 01:06:37.930 align:middle line:10%
brings acceptance.

01:06:37.930 --> 01:06:42.420 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I tell them, if
you see a tree that is 2 feet,

01:06:42.420 --> 01:06:46.050 align:middle line:84%
that tree is not ashamed
because another tree is 10.

01:06:46.050 --> 01:06:47.070 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: (LAUGHING) Right.

01:06:47.070 --> 01:06:51.960 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Because that tree
understands that in its 2 feet,

01:06:51.960 --> 01:06:55.290 align:middle line:84%
that is the height
of its present glory

01:06:55.290 --> 01:06:58.130 align:middle line:90%
and it is going to keep going.

01:06:58.130 --> 01:07:01.500 align:middle line:84%
Any time you feel ashamed
for your position in life,

01:07:01.500 --> 01:07:04.420 align:middle line:84%
you interfere with
your potential.

01:07:04.420 --> 01:07:08.980 align:middle line:84%
So self-acceptance,
understanding the larger

01:07:08.980 --> 01:07:13.120 align:middle line:84%
picture, and know that it's a
journey makes you not beat down

01:07:13.120 --> 01:07:13.920 align:middle line:90%
on yourself.

01:07:13.920 --> 01:07:14.570 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Yeah.

01:07:14.570 --> 01:07:16.250 align:middle line:84%
The tree doesn't have
an opinion of itself.

01:07:16.250 --> 01:07:16.420 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yeah.

01:07:16.420 --> 01:07:17.070 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

01:07:17.070 --> 01:07:18.725 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: We cultivate opinions
about ourselves, which--

01:07:18.725 --> 01:07:19.735 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: Yeah, It's
just being a tree.

01:07:19.735 --> 01:07:20.140 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: --stops it.

01:07:20.140 --> 01:07:20.920 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:07:20.920 --> 01:07:22.545 align:middle line:84%
We learn and awaken
through resistance.

01:07:22.545 --> 01:07:25.060 align:middle line:84%
This is what you're
saying, that don't back off

01:07:25.060 --> 01:07:26.290 align:middle line:90%
when there is resistance.

01:07:26.290 --> 01:07:28.595 align:middle line:84%
Learn and grow and
allow that power--

01:07:28.595 --> 01:07:29.530 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: The push.

01:07:29.530 --> 01:07:33.353 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: --and the push to be
your guide, to be your path.

01:07:33.353 --> 01:07:35.020 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So I sometimes
put it this way.

01:07:35.020 --> 01:07:39.580 align:middle line:84%
I say, if you see a flower
coming out and it's pushing

01:07:39.580 --> 01:07:42.580 align:middle line:90%
and you go and open the pedal--

01:07:42.580 --> 01:07:45.862 align:middle line:84%
the outer one-- that
plant is stunted.

01:07:45.862 --> 01:07:47.320 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Yeah, it
won't do its thing.

01:07:47.320 --> 01:07:52.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: So the idea of
love, the idea of supporting

01:07:52.510 --> 01:07:54.550 align:middle line:84%
each other, does not
mean we should take away

01:07:54.550 --> 01:07:58.390 align:middle line:84%
the individual's power
for self-determination.

01:07:58.390 --> 01:08:00.610 align:middle line:90%
It is important, the push.

01:08:00.610 --> 01:08:04.360 align:middle line:84%
But you just need the support
to do the pushing ourselves.

01:08:04.360 --> 01:08:09.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, accepting what is is
part of finding harmony

01:08:09.880 --> 01:08:13.100 align:middle line:90%
with what you are.

01:08:13.100 --> 01:08:16.050 align:middle line:90%
The moment we hate the journey--

01:08:16.050 --> 01:08:17.819 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Yes, love
is the key, right.

01:08:17.819 --> 01:08:17.979 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: [LAUGHS]

01:08:17.979 --> 01:08:19.510 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: I call it the
universal solvent.

01:08:19.510 --> 01:08:19.600 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Yup.

01:08:19.600 --> 01:08:21.152 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Everything
dissolves in love.

01:08:21.152 --> 01:08:22.069 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Love, mm-hmm.

01:08:22.069 --> 01:08:24.790 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: So in this
exchange of love,

01:08:24.790 --> 01:08:27.340 align:middle line:84%
we know that
community is easier.

01:08:27.340 --> 01:08:29.140 align:middle line:84%
We know that
bonding through love

01:08:29.140 --> 01:08:33.220 align:middle line:84%
generates community faster
versus trying to make our way

01:08:33.220 --> 01:08:35.729 align:middle line:84%
and be competitive
and earn our way in--

01:08:35.729 --> 01:08:37.029 align:middle line:90%
just to love our way into it.

01:08:37.029 --> 01:08:41.319 align:middle line:10%
Can you speak about how
healing through community

01:08:41.319 --> 01:08:43.711 align:middle line:10%
can truly heal the world?

01:08:43.711 --> 01:08:49.370 align:middle line:90%


01:08:49.370 --> 01:08:52.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SOWAH: I think
there's no other way.

01:08:52.180 --> 01:08:56.279 align:middle line:84%
There's no other way to
be well in isolation.

01:08:56.279 --> 01:09:05.220 align:middle line:10%
And I feel that our current
paradigm fosters competition,

01:09:05.220 --> 01:09:07.770 align:middle line:10%
individualism, and isolation.

01:09:07.770 --> 01:09:12.830 align:middle line:10%
And that process makes
us go fast sometimes.

01:09:12.830 --> 01:09:16.470 align:middle line:84%
But there is an African
proverb that says this.

01:09:16.470 --> 01:09:20.315 align:middle line:84%
If you want to go
fast, go alone.

01:09:20.315 --> 01:09:24.779 align:middle line:10%
But if you want to go
far, go in community.

01:09:24.779 --> 01:09:29.970 align:middle line:84%
How do we ensure that
every step we take

01:09:29.970 --> 01:09:35.479 align:middle line:84%
is really a forward step and
not a backward one, or just

01:09:35.479 --> 01:09:37.479 align:middle line:90%
a step only to fall back?

01:09:37.479 --> 01:09:44.390 align:middle line:84%
And so I think, in my little
way, I am using dance,

01:09:44.390 --> 01:09:48.359 align:middle line:84%
I'm using singing, I'm using
storytelling and the community

01:09:48.359 --> 01:09:53.390 align:middle line:84%
circle as a metaphor for
reimagining a better world--

01:09:53.390 --> 01:09:58.520 align:middle line:84%
a world that is consistent
with the divine principles that

01:09:58.520 --> 01:10:01.410 align:middle line:90%
guide our lives.

01:10:01.410 --> 01:10:05.690 align:middle line:84%
And I think when we depart from
the natural contours of life,

01:10:05.690 --> 01:10:09.590 align:middle line:84%
we build something magnificent,
only for it to fall apart.

01:10:09.590 --> 01:10:16.070 align:middle line:84%
So I am interested
in inspiring students

01:10:16.070 --> 01:10:20.200 align:middle line:84%
to begin to question
their purpose in life,

01:10:20.200 --> 01:10:21.220 align:middle line:90%
their place in life.

01:10:21.220 --> 01:10:22.270 align:middle line:90%
What are you?

01:10:22.270 --> 01:10:25.690 align:middle line:84%
And how are you
participating in creating

01:10:25.690 --> 01:10:29.470 align:middle line:84%
a more livable, sustainable,
and peaceful world?

01:10:29.470 --> 01:10:32.620 align:middle line:10%
Healing is not about me, me, me.

01:10:32.620 --> 01:10:34.300 align:middle line:90%
Healing is a matrix.

01:10:34.300 --> 01:10:35.980 align:middle line:90%
We are interconnected.

01:10:35.980 --> 01:10:40.282 align:middle line:84%
And our health depends on
our interconnectedness.

01:10:40.282 --> 01:10:41.365 align:middle line:90%
>>SUE: Thank you so much--

01:10:41.365 --> 01:10:41.620 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Thank you.

01:10:41.620 --> 01:10:43.930 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: --for what you are
bringing to this world

01:10:43.930 --> 01:10:46.450 align:middle line:84%
and weaving things
back together again.

01:10:46.450 --> 01:10:50.140 align:middle line:84%
I don't think anyone will
ever look at dance and song

01:10:50.140 --> 01:10:54.700 align:middle line:84%
and music the same again after
they hear this conversation.

01:10:54.700 --> 01:10:56.450 align:middle line:84%
It is most beautiful
and most significant.

01:10:56.450 --> 01:10:57.950 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for being with us.

01:10:57.950 --> 01:10:58.810 align:middle line:90%
>>SOWAH: Thank you.

01:10:58.810 --> 01:11:00.190 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

01:11:00.190 --> 01:11:02.920 align:middle line:84%
>>SUE: Medicine is not the only
way you can heal your body.

01:11:02.920 --> 01:11:05.110 align:middle line:84%
And healing doesn't
have to be painful.

01:11:05.110 --> 01:11:06.910 align:middle line:90%
It can be joyful.

01:11:06.910 --> 01:11:09.700 align:middle line:84%
If we suffer physically,
emotionally, and spiritually,

01:11:09.700 --> 01:11:12.660 align:middle line:84%
we don't need to mend
those wounds alone.

01:11:12.660 --> 01:11:16.390 align:middle line:84%
What Nii Armah is
doing is proof that we

01:11:16.390 --> 01:11:18.640 align:middle line:90%
heal best within community.

01:11:18.640 --> 01:11:21.580 align:middle line:84%
Because after all,
we are all connected.

